1
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:44,750
"'Would anyone give their life
for a language', you ask?"

2
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,916
"Languages aren't just sounds
and alphabets."

3
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:49,541
"It is the breath of a race."

4
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:51,125
"It is an identity."

5
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:56,041
"England obliterated the Gaelic language
when they occupied and enslaved Scotland."

6
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:59,791
"The day Mikhail Gorbachev decreed Russian
to be the sole language for all..."

7
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:02,750
"...there was heavy resistance
in the Soviet Union."

8
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:08,000
"The day Jinnah imposed Urdu as the
sole language in East and West Pakistan..."

9
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,666
"...people began demanding their rights."

10
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:15,291
"This brand of fanaticism took root
in India for the first time in 1918."

11
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:18,375
"By claiming English to be
an oppressor's language..."

12
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:22,541
"...the Indian leaders up north
decided everyone must speak Hindi."

13
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:27,291
"They proceeded to covertly and overtly
implement this imposition."

14
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,291
"Those who resisted this change
were arrested en masse."

15
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:33,000
"They were assaulted and tortured."

16
00:04:33,416 --> 00:04:35,375
"When fear arose about
the Hindi imposition..."

17
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:38,666
"...leaving the studies, jobs,
and lives of many in dire straits..."

18
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:41,750
"When it was believed there were none left
to rally against this..."

19
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:44,500
"...an army rose up
to protect their mother tongue."

20
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,875
"A army of students
that knew no fear."

21
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:48,875
"The Puranaanooru Squad."

22
00:05:24,541 --> 00:05:28,791
He was part of the very first batch
trained in espionage by Russia's KGB, sir.

23
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:31,250
One of the finest and sharpest officers
we have.

24
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,500
Officer Thiru.
Thirunadan.

25
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:36,000
KGB, huh?

26
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:37,166
You must be brilliant.

27
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:39,916
I am what I am.

28
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:44,500
Who is that arrogant prick?

29
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:46,916
Sir!
Ibrahim Kamal, IPS.

30
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:48,250
Madras Liaison Officer.

31
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:49,416
At your service, sir.

32
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:50,791
Just got on at the last station.

33
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,500
Sir?

34
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,125
Don't, Chezhiya!
Fall back!

35
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,750
Should we die for a language?

36
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:28,000
Then what? Should we keep bowing to them
for life?

37
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:29,916
We must strike back!
We must create history!

38
00:06:30,541 --> 00:06:33,250
We're fighting for your language too,
Govind!

39
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:35,291
Join us if you want!
If you're scared, run away!

40
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:37,000
You'll die!
Please listen to me!

41
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:38,291
Back away!
-Chezhiya!

42
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,916
'Fire up your intellect
and make your foes tremble'

43
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:44,000
'Sharpen your core
and erupt like a volcano'

44
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:45,625
'Ours is a great army'

45
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,666
'Bear witness, for ours is a great army'

46
00:06:48,791 --> 00:06:50,250
Ibrahim!
-Yes, sir?

47
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:52,500
Make sure all three VIP coaches
are protected!

48
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:55,875
'Bring your hands together
and bolster the army'

49
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,791
'Fall as a seed
and make the world bloom'

50
00:06:58,916 --> 00:07:01,625
'Ours is a great army'

51
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,416
'Bear witness, for ours is a great army'

52
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:08,000
There are too many of them.

53
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:09,875
Never mind the protestors.

54
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:11,875
Protect the ministers.

55
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,250
Okay, sir.
Come on!

56
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:19,500
'Fire up your intellect
and make your foes tremble'

57
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:22,750
'Sharpen your core
and erupt like a volcano'

58
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,250
'Ours is a great army'

59
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,166
Come on!
-'Ours is a great army'

60
00:07:26,291 --> 00:07:27,375
Hurry!

61
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,666
Make it fast!

62
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:34,625
(Let justice prevail)

63
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,875
Get everyone out, Major!

64
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,791
Nobody must remain in the compartment!
This is Major's order!

65
00:07:42,916 --> 00:07:45,166
(Telugu) "Major"?
He didn't clear the last selection!

66
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:47,875
(Telugu) Just a "Minor!"
-You'll salute this Major one day!

67
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,291
Nobody panic!
Leave calmly!

68
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:50,500
(Malayalam) Go quickly!

69
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:52,375
(Bengali) Careful!

70
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:53,791
Get going!

71
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,750
Come along, I say!

72
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:57,250
Come on!
-(Hindi) Let go of my hand!

73
00:07:57,375 --> 00:07:59,250
Hold on!
-(Hindi) Don't be scared!

74
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:00,500
You needn't be afraid!

75
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,250
You needn't be afraid, ma'am!
We're...

76
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:05,041
We're only fighting the imposition
of Hindi!

77
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:07,000
We're not against Hindi or its speakers!

78
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,541
Please don't cry.
Don't be afraid.

79
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:13,666
Tell me what I need to do.

80
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,500
Get them out of here safely, Govind.

81
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:25,541
'Fire up your intellect
and make your foes tremble'

82
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:28,750
Go to Madurai and lay low at home,
Govind.

83
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,291
I'll send word! Come later!
-Okay!

84
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:33,000
Ensure he leaves safe!
I'll check if there's anyone left behind!

85
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:36,291
Sir!

86
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:40,500
'Bring your hands together
and bolster the army'

87
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:42,250
(Let justice prevail)

88
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:44,000
'Fall as a seed
and make the world bloom'

89
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:45,541
'Ours is a great army'

90
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:47,666
'Bear witness, for ours is a great army'

91
00:08:47,791 --> 00:08:49,750
Govind's left, hasn't he?
-He left with Aavudai!

92
00:08:49,875 --> 00:08:52,000
Hurry!
No one should get caught by the police!

93
00:09:45,125 --> 00:09:48,625
Long Live the Prime Minister!

94
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:51,416
I proudly welcome the citizens of Madurai
who are here today...

95
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:53,541
...for the inauguration of
the Gandhi Memorial!

96
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:56,750
Our beloved Prime Minister
has arrived!

97
00:09:56,875 --> 00:09:58,000
Welcome, sir.
Make way!

98
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:02,750
(Hindi) Who did this?

99
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:06,375
Hooligans from the opposition.
We'll get them.

100
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,125
No one to beat them, sir!
Top class work!

101
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:11,625
The fire was made by people
who know chemistry. It spreads fast!

102
00:10:12,125 --> 00:10:14,875
They've planned their next moves
thoroughly.

103
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,916
They stopped the train between two stations
so they'd have an easy escape.

104
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:21,250
They wrapped it up in just six minutes
and took off.

105
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:23,250
Tamil fanatics, huh?

106
00:10:23,375 --> 00:10:24,500
Not exactly.

107
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:27,666
Malayalam, Telugu, Kannada, Bengali
and Marathi speaking students!

108
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:28,875
About twenty in all!

109
00:10:30,125 --> 00:10:31,625
I think it's a student movement, sir.

110
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:33,625
Spread across the country.

111
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:37,625
Mr. Prime Minister,
this act seems to be for political gain.

112
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:39,750
Wait outside, Thiru.

113
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,750
Thiru?

114
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:46,250
Sir...

115
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:49,125
There were railway job openings
listed in Hindi newspapers.

116
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,625
But not in the Tamil ones.

117
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,166
This is what provoked the students.

118
00:10:52,291 --> 00:10:53,541
So, they burned the train.

119
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:55,000
This is purely reactionary.

120
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:57,041
But, sir...

121
00:10:58,250 --> 00:10:59,500
We must hunt them down!

122
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:01,291
They should be eradicated.

123
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
No.

124
00:11:03,125 --> 00:11:05,500
This issue can't be solved
with violence.

125
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:08,250
It shouldn't give rise
to more dissenters.

126
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:12,875
I want this incident to be depicted
as nothing but a fire accident.

127
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Understood?

128
00:11:17,291 --> 00:11:18,291
Thiru!

129
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:23,166
(Sanskrit) "Alertness Every Moment".

130
00:11:23,666 --> 00:11:24,666
Always alert.

131
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:27,000
That's the IB's motto, right?

132
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:32,666
Did someone steal your revolver,
or did you give it away to your comrades?

133
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:34,875
(Hindi) Hold up!

134
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:36,750
How can you fire it...

135
00:11:37,375 --> 00:11:40,250
...when the Tamil blood of your father
runs in your veins?

136
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:42,250
You're not just any misbegot.

137
00:11:42,375 --> 00:11:43,875
You are a Madrasi misbegot.

138
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:50,541
You have an accurate summary
of my blood report.

139
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:53,625
Had you been as thorough
with the ground report...

140
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:56,250
...we could've avoided all this,
Chief of Intelligence.

141
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:58,916
You're the one who gave the false report,
wasn't it?

142
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:00,375
This isn't over!

143
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,666
You'll face an enquiry for this!
You will pay for this!

144
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,541
"It has come to my attention..."

145
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:10,166
...that my brethren
from the Southern states...

146
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:14,500
"...are troubled
by the Official Languages Act."

147
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:16,875
"Should they be forced
to only speak in Hindi..."

148
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,666
"...in official correspondence
with the government..."

149
00:12:20,125 --> 00:12:22,791
...I understand the fear of those
in non-Hindi speaking regions...

150
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:26,875
"...of being denied access
to welfare schemes..."

151
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,000
...and opportunities
they rightfully deserve.

152
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:33,666
"I truly comprehend and sympathize
with your emotions."

153
00:12:33,791 --> 00:12:36,000
"Until all non-Hindi speaking states..."

154
00:12:36,125 --> 00:12:40,166
"...give their unanimous consent to accept
Hindi as the official language..."

155
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:45,166
"...I pledge that English shall continue
to be an official language until 1965."

156
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:46,291
"And will remain so..."

157
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:48,625
...even beyond that.
You have my word.

158
00:12:51,166 --> 00:12:52,375
Tamilarasan!
-Present, sir!

159
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,291
'She, who is as sweet as Tamil...'
-Muthiah!

160
00:12:54,416 --> 00:12:56,416
You heard the song!
A fight fete is about to start!

161
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:58,375
'She, who is like a flowering vine...'

162
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:01,541
'She, who is like a flowering vine
that smiles like the moon'

163
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:06,875
'With her honey lips,
she will endow the essence of life'

164
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,250
'As you savor it drop by drop,
she will bend her head shyly'

165
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,416
'She, who is as sweet as Tamil...'

166
00:13:14,541 --> 00:13:17,625
'She, who is like a flowering vine
that smiles like the moon'

167
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:21,666
'She, who is like a flowering vine
that smiles like the moon'

168
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:25,416
Freedom!
Isn't that what we want?

169
00:13:25,541 --> 00:13:26,541
Yes!

170
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:28,625
One can have love for a language!

171
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:31,000
But what you are possessed by
is language fanaticism!

172
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:33,666
We see Tamil only as a language, sir!

173
00:13:33,791 --> 00:13:35,541
They're the ones turning it
to fanaticism.

174
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:39,625
Think we'll let trains enter our town when
railway jobs aren't listed in Tamil papers?

175
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,875
When none of us can get those jobs,
how can we permit it?

176
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,000
How can we?

177
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:44,125
We won't!

178
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:46,041
Never mind!
Such ads used to come in English!

179
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:47,875
We only asked why they were discontinued!

180
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,375
English is an alien language.

181
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,666
To us, everything but Tamil
is an alien language!

182
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:55,625
Isn't Hindi an alien language
in many states?

183
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,375
With English, you can talk to anyone
in the world, Mr. Principal!

184
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,625
Why are you getting mixed up
with these kids, Mr. Tamil Professor?

185
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:06,291
Wouldn't it be helpful to the government,
if we all speak the same language?

186
00:14:06,416 --> 00:14:07,916
For national unity, right?

187
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,166
Mr. Principal!

188
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,916
We were united
when we sent the British packing!

189
00:14:13,041 --> 00:14:14,875
Were we all speaking the same language
then?

190
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,000
No!

191
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,541
Answer Chezhiyan, sir!

192
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:20,000
No matter how he protests,
he's still the college topper!

193
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,166
These guys are Delhi politicians!

194
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:24,666
That's their vow for now.
Don't trust them.

195
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:27,625
If they break their vow,
their domain will be torched next!

196
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:29,875
The vow of the students!

197
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
We always walk the talk!

198
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:33,666
Yes, we will!
-Good grief...

199
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:35,125
Yes, we will!

200
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,750
Can I carry that for you, sir?

201
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:39,625
Move aside!

202
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:42,875
Mr. Principal doesn't need English,
but only needs English cars!

203
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,791
'The time is ours...'

204
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:55,666
'With the speed of fire'

205
00:14:57,416 --> 00:15:00,250
'Unhating courage...
Worthy sacrifice...'

206
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:01,750
'Let's stand for our language'

207
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,875
'Strap on those wings and step up'

208
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,666
'Hit that beat and sing your heart away'

209
00:15:10,916 --> 00:15:13,000
'Directions eight will join hands,
because of you'

210
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:18,750
'Our blood is on fire'

211
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,791
'The crowds roar
when your name is heard'

212
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:24,916
'Our nation shall triumph,
because of us'

213
00:15:37,875 --> 00:15:39,166
(Long Live Tamil)

214
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,500
'Every town is our own'

215
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:54,291
'Tomorrow is ours for the taking'

216
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,875
'When hands join together as one...'

217
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:00,125
'...anything is possible now on'

218
00:16:01,541 --> 00:16:04,166
'If we all just tend to our homes,
who will tend to our nation?'

219
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:06,375
'Charge in with all your might'

220
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:10,375
'No town an alien land...
No person a stranger...'

221
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:12,250
'Come on, comrade...
Let's begin'

222
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:16,250
'Celebrate like never before,
for that is our culture'

223
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:19,375
'Should anyone come to divide us,
step up and question them'

224
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,125
'Keep moving forward...
As our ancestors taught us'

225
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,666
'Their good words guide us onward'

