00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:46,750
The Young Lawyers Association will fight
for justice of students for no fee!

248
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:47,916
That's my lawyer for you!

249
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:49,375
How's our legal counsel, sir?

250
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,125
Is that why you studied 'Brahmi'
with me?

251
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,250
Hey Aavudai!

252
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,166
Where's Govind?

253
00:17:58,875 --> 00:17:59,875
Chezhiya...

254
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:04,375
"The train transporting central ministers
to Madurai met with a fire accident."

255
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,000
"A student passenger burned to death."

256
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,625
With your name constantly on his lips...

257
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:17,125
...he'd always be right by your side!

258
00:18:17,541 --> 00:18:20,875
And yet, you stand here without him!

259
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:23,625
What are you saying, mom?

260
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:26,375
You think Chezhiya would've let this happen
to Govind?

261
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:29,750
Chezhiya is one of us, mom!

262
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,000
(Saurashtra) He's family!

263
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:33,291
Come in, Chezhiya!

264
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:36,125
No, Chezhiya! We'll slip and fall!
-Hurry!

265
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,750
I'll bring him back safely every vacation,
auntie!

266
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,166
(Saurashtra) Travel safe, dear!

267
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:45,791
Come!
-(Saurashtra) Bye, grandma!

268
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,541
(Saurashtra) Take care!
-Be safe, dear!

269
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,375
You'd never have come if I hadn't called!

270
00:19:12,791 --> 00:19:13,791
Hello?

271
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:15,250
Brother Thambi?

272
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:19,666
Chezhiya?

273
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:23,041
Michael Reddy, Shariffa,
Chacko and Bindhya...

274
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:25,125
They're safe at Thambiraja's mill
in Pollachi.

275
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,500
They asked if they have to come.

276
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:27,916
What do I tell them?

277
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:30,250
(Hindi) Clench your fists.

278
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:32,000
Your pulses are very weak.

279
00:19:32,125 --> 00:19:34,875
Your nerves have been damaged.
You will need an amputation.

280
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:37,375
No!

281
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,500
Stitch it up!

282
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:39,875
What are you doing, Thiru?

283
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,000
What's your problem?

284
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,541
You slept with a Tamilian
and gave birth to me!

285
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,125
Once he was satisfied, he abandoned you!

286
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:50,375
Thanks to another Tamilian,
I lost an arm!

287
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,125
How will I fire now?

288
00:19:54,125 --> 00:19:55,750
It's our Puranaanooru Squad.

289
00:19:56,166 --> 00:19:57,875
Shall I ask them to come, Chezhiya?

290
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,041
No one needs to come anymore.

291
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:06,375
I'm not ready to lose anyone else.

292
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:12,166
As of now,
I'm nothing but a Tamil-speaking cripple!

293
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:13,916
A Madrasi traitor!

294
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:16,375
If that's what you believe...

295
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:20,750
...the world will continue to belittle you
and mock at you!

296
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:25,625
The Puranaanooru Squad is no more!

297
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:26,875
Understood?
-Chezhiya!

298
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,291
No more money orders, protests...
No nothing!

299
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:32,250
The Puranaanooru Squad is dead!

300
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:35,875
Mom?

301
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,625
I accept who I am.

302
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:47,125
I don't want anyone else to die
because of me!

303
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:59,666
I don't want anyone else to die
because of me...

304
00:21:03,125 --> 00:21:04,916
"The Supreme Power."

305
00:21:32,125 --> 00:21:34,000
Brother!
Turn off that valve!

306
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:36,000
If the pressure rises, it'll explode!

307
00:21:36,125 --> 00:21:38,375
(Hindi) What? Everything's fine!
What are you saying?

308
00:21:40,166 --> 00:21:41,500
(Broken Hindi) "What happened?"

309
00:21:42,291 --> 00:21:44,000
Had it blown up,
you'd be in pieces!

310
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:45,541
You'd have killed 250 people too!

311
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:48,916
"Engine blowback"!
Didn't they teach you that?

312
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:51,666
You'd have been toasted!
-(Hindi) What?

313
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,250
(Hindi) Speak in Hindi, Madrasi!

314
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:55,416
(Hindi) From January 26th,
you'll have no choice!

315
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:58,875
(Broken Tamil) You must speak it then!
For now, just do your job, fireman!

316
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
(Hindi) Got it?

317
00:22:00,750 --> 00:22:02,125
Nothing's going to change!

318
00:22:03,291 --> 00:22:04,375
Just watch!

319
00:22:05,416 --> 00:22:07,875
The PM maybe no more, but his vow
to the Parliament still is!

320
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,000
(Hindi) What?

321
00:22:09,125 --> 00:22:10,541
Back to Hindi, eh?

322
00:22:11,416 --> 00:22:14,750
(Broken Hindi) Lal! When a Madrasi
goes to Delhi, he'll talk in Hindi!

323
00:22:15,166 --> 00:22:18,000
(Broken Hindi) When a Hindi guy
comes to Madurai, he must talk in Tamil!

324
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:19,250
(Broken Hindi) Got it?

325
00:22:19,375 --> 00:22:21,875
(Hindi) Madurai... Madrasi...
What?

326
00:22:23,041 --> 00:22:24,041
Chow down!

327
00:22:26,625 --> 00:22:28,166
(Hindi) This fritter is delicious!

328
00:22:28,291 --> 00:22:29,291
How's that?

329
00:22:30,166 --> 00:22:32,500
You don't want Tamil,
but you want our fritters, eh?

330
00:22:33,125 --> 00:22:34,166
Your whack is waiting!

331
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,375
(Hindi) Come again, Madrasi?

332
00:22:46,166 --> 00:22:47,750
Two one pennies!

333
00:22:47,875 --> 00:22:48,875
Goddamn it!

334
00:22:49,375 --> 00:22:51,875
Don't say it like that, you dumbos!
-How else then?

335
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,541
"One penny plus one penny
equal two pennies."

336
00:22:54,666 --> 00:22:56,416
One penny plus one penny
equal two pennies!

337
00:22:56,541 --> 00:22:57,750
Don't shout, sillies!

338
00:22:57,875 --> 00:22:59,916
"Due to the death
of the Indian Prime Minister..."

339
00:23:00,041 --> 00:23:03,250
"...the last twelve days were declared
to be a period of mourning nationwide."

340
00:23:03,375 --> 00:23:04,625
"It comes to an end today."

341
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:07,500
What a good man!

342
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,666
Without warning, he left us all!

343
00:23:10,541 --> 00:23:12,750
You thought he'd die
after a heart-to-heart with you?

344
00:23:14,125 --> 00:23:16,250
The Telugu girl from next door
has arrived!

345
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:19,000
Her eyes and ears
are always here!

346
00:23:20,125 --> 00:23:23,500
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

347
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:27,000
What are you staring at there?
-(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

348
00:23:29,416 --> 00:23:30,875
Good grief!
She's at it again!

349
00:23:32,166 --> 00:23:33,875
Kid!

350
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,291
Chezhiyan will be here soon!

351
00:23:35,416 --> 00:23:36,541
Why try to fix it yourself?

352
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:38,625
You don't need him for this!

353
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:39,875
(Telugu) I got it!

354
00:23:41,041 --> 00:23:42,541
Careful, Ratna!

355
00:23:42,666 --> 00:23:45,291
Easy does it!
-Just take this wire...

356
00:23:45,416 --> 00:23:46,750
...and stick it in like this.

357
00:23:47,625 --> 00:23:48,625
All done!

358
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:50,375
All done, indeed!

359
00:23:51,375 --> 00:23:52,541
Why's the power out, grandma?

360
00:23:52,666 --> 00:23:55,500
Only one bulb was flickering.

361
00:23:55,625 --> 00:23:58,625
She just had to mess with it!

362
00:23:58,750 --> 00:24:00,500
The entire house went dark!
-She's had it!

363
00:24:00,625 --> 00:24:02,125
She truly has the magic touch!

364
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:05,250
Didn't I tell you not to let her in here,
grandma?

365
00:24:05,875 --> 00:24:06,875
Like I let her in!

366
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:09,375
Want to pull wires?
Do it at your house!

367
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:11,250
I will if you get out of my way,
tosser!

368
00:24:11,375 --> 00:24:12,666
Who are you calling 'tosser'?

369
00:24:12,791 --> 00:24:14,291
You toss coal, right?

370
00:24:14,416 --> 00:24:15,416
Coal tosser!

371
00:24:16,791 --> 00:24:18,791
Why do I even talk to this creature?

372
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,000
Dinner ready, grandma?

373
00:24:22,125 --> 00:24:24,250
It's been ready for a while!
The same tamarind stew!

374
00:24:25,250 --> 00:24:26,250
It's back!

375
00:24:26,375 --> 00:24:28,375
There's a letter for you, Chezhiya!

376
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:29,500
A letter?

377
00:24:29,625 --> 00:24:30,625
Where is it?

378
00:24:31,291 --> 00:24:32,291
Here!
-Let me see!

379
00:24:41,041 --> 00:24:42,500
Who is it from?

380
00:24:48,791 --> 00:24:51,125
Your grandson's going to become
a ticket examiner!

381
00:24:51,250 --> 00:24:52,666
He's being called for an interview!

382
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:54,500
Posting's in Delhi!
-Really?

383
00:24:55,625 --> 00:24:59,250
If anyone calls me a coal tosser again,
tell them I'll rip their tongue out!

384
00:25:00,750 --> 00:25:01,875
You just have to learn Hindi!

385
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,750
Hindi, huh?

386
00:25:03,875 --> 00:25:06,375
That's a hopeless cause
for our entire clan!

387
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:09,250
I sent you to three teachers
when you were a kid.

388
00:25:09,375 --> 00:25:12,000
You couldn't even get three words right!

389
00:25:12,125 --> 00:25:13,750
I couldn't because I didn't need it then!

390
00:25:13,875 --> 00:25:16,375
Wherever you go to work,
you must learn the local language!

391
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:19,416
Then how am I any different
from that Hindi speaking loco pilot?

392
00:25:20,041 --> 00:25:22,500
Don't you know Hindi well, Telugu girl?

393
00:25:22,625 --> 00:25:23,791
Why don't you teach him?

394
00:25:23,916 --> 00:25:25,166
Who? Her?

395
00:25:25,791 --> 00:25:28,500
I'd rather shovel coal for life
than learn Hindi from her!

396
00:25:28,625 --> 00:25:30,250
There's the Hindi Federation, right?

397
00:25:30,916 --> 00:25:33,250
I'm your only option
in this entire locality!

398
00:25:33,875 --> 00:25:35,166
But I can't teach you!

399
00:25:35,291 --> 00:25:36,416
Pay for a course and learn!

400
00:25:36,916 --> 00:25:39,750
It's late. I have an important
news recording in the morning.

401
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:43,000
Trains will run without him.

402
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:45,291
Even the government will run
without my father!

403
00:25:45,416 --> 00:25:49,750
But without Ratnamala,
the National Radio will be at a standstill!

404
00:25:50,375 --> 00:25:52,125
Understand that!
Move, tosser!

405
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:53,250
Ratna!

406
00:25:53,875 --> 00:25:56,000
I've never once heard your voice
on the radio!

407
00:25:56,791 --> 00:25:58,750
What station should I connect to?
-What, indeed?

408
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:01,666
First, disconnect that deaf ear of yours!

409
00:26:02,125 --> 00:26:03,125
The mouth on this girl!

410
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:04,625
What did she say?

411
00:26:05,625 --> 00:26:06,916
Come feed me dinner!

412
00:26:07,625 --> 00:26:09,125
They've closed down colleges.

413
00:26:09,250 --> 00:26:10,375
Durai's not home yet?

414
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:13,166
Like he ever tells me when he comes
and goes!

415
00:26:14,041 --> 00:26:16,250
He roams around town like a jackass!

416
00:26:16,375 --> 00:26:19,750
You slog in that oven all day for him
and come here dark as the night!

417
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,000
After raking coal all day,
you expect me to shine like the moon?

418
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,750
He's at the top of his class.

419
00:26:26,875 --> 00:26:27,916
Don't scold him.

420
00:26:30,416 --> 00:26:32,375
I can understand sending it
to Govind's family.

421
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:35,375
But why send money to your brother
when he's not even asking for it?

422
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:38,541
You took loans all over town
to make him study!

423
00:26:39,125 --> 00:26:40,500
Does he ever think about that?

424
00:26:41,625 --> 00:26:42,875
Will you serve dinner or not?

425
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,375
He needn't think about anything!

426
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:47,166
It's good enough if he becomes an engineer
and works a cushy job!

427
00:26:47,291 --> 00:26:48,500
As long as he does that, good.

428
00:26:48,625 --> 00:26:49,625
Serve dinner!

429
00:26:51,291 --> 00:26:52,875
National Radio!

430
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,375
Greetings!
-Greetings, dear!

431
00:26:56,000 --> 00:27:00,000
(Telugu) 'The man's world quakes'

432
00:27:00,125 --> 00:27:02,750
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

433
00:27:02,875 --> 00:27:03,875
Please move, ma'am.

434
00:27:04,291 --> 00:27:05,625
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk...'

435
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,375
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

436
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:08,500
Your tea, sir.

437
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:10,500
Greetings, ma'am.

438
00:27:10,625 --> 00:27:11,791
Good Morning, ma'am!

439
00:27:12,250 --> 00:27:13,250
Greetings, ma'am!

440
00:27:13,375 --> 00:27:14,625
Good Morning, ma'am!

441
00:27:15,791 --> 00:27:18,875
(Telugu) 'The man's world quakes'

442
00:27:19,375 --> 00:27:22,041
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

443
00:27:22,875 --> 00:27:24,791
(Telugu) 'The man's world quakes'

444
00:27:32,416 --> 00:27:35,125
Who told you to clean the windows,
miss?

445
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:39,125
Your father will sack me if he learns
you're not doing the announcer job!

446
00:27:39,250 --> 00:27:40,875
Just once come to the studio!
Read this!

447
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,500
Me?
-Yes! Look!

448
00:27:42,625 --> 00:27:44,250
Just seeing a mic paralyzes me!

449
00:27:44,375 --> 00:27:45,541
You can do it!
-I'll stammer!

450
00:27:45,666 --> 00:27:47,625
Just read this once!
-You already know that!

451
00:27:47,750 --> 00:27:49,000
You can do it! Just try!
-Sir!

452
00:27:55,625 --> 00:27:57,875
Goo... Good Morning.
Here's the morning news.

453
00:27:58,875 --> 00:27:59,916
Excellent!

454
00:28:01,125 --> 00:28:05,500
The central government's
key obj... objective..

455
00:28:08,375 --> 00:28:11,000
...is progress through peace.

456
00:28:11,625 --> 00:28:12,625
Lovely!

457
00:28:13,625 --> 00:28:14,875
A new...

458
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:17,750
...sch... scheme...

459
00:28:21,125 --> 00:28:23,125
She thinks she can go on the air
with that stutter!

460
00:28:23,250 --> 00:28:26,375
...has been implem... implemented...

461
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:27,666
Miss?
-...and...

462
00:28:27,791 --> 00:28:30,416
She has come here using influence
and is torturing us. So useless!

463
00:28:33,125 --> 00:28:34,750
Didn't I tell you, sir?
-Tell me what?

464
00:28:34,875 --> 00:28:37,041
Rest assured,
I won't tell my father about this!

465
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:11,625
Hold on!

466
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:15,541
Fill mine in first, sister. I'll have to
send money to my grandson at college.

467
00:29:15,666 --> 00:29:17,000
Such a stubborn one!

468
00:29:17,125 --> 00:29:19,500
He'd rather starve to death
than ask for money!

469
00:29:19,625 --> 00:29:20,625
Fill mine!
-Wait!

470
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:23,250
My son's hands are sore
from working at the tannery!

471
00:29:23,375 --> 00:29:25,000
I need to send money
so he can buy medicine.

472
00:29:25,125 --> 00:29:26,500
Look what these morons have done!

473
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:30,041
What is this?

474
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:32,250
Move.
-Ask them yourself!

475
00:29:32,375 --> 00:29:33,500
What language is this?

476
00:29:33,625 --> 00:29:35,791
You've given the wrong form.
I need the Tamil one!

477
00:29:35,916 --> 00:29:39,291
This is how it is now, ma'am.
By order of the central government.

478
00:29:39,750 --> 00:29:41,000
What language is this?

479
00:29:43,875 --> 00:29:45,125
It's Hindi, ma'am.

480
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:47,541
The central government has made
these forms mandatory.

481
00:29:48,541 --> 00:29:51,375
I'm the one sending money.
My grandson's the one receiving it.

482
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,125
Neither of us know this language,
dear fellow!

483
00:29:54,750 --> 00:29:56,000
Fill it out yourself!

484
00:29:56,125 --> 00:30:00,500
Wouldn't we have become ministers in Delhi
if we knew Hindi, ma'am?

485
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,875
You useless nincompoops!

486
00:30:03,541 --> 00:30:06,666
So we'll have to personally go to Delhi
to send money orders?

487
00:30:07,916 --> 00:30:08,916
Come along!

488
00:30:09,041 --> 00:30:10,500
Nothing to discuss here! Let's go!

489
00:30:10,625 --> 00:30:12,375
Come along! Hurry!
-Way to give us trouble!

490
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:15,166
What will my grandson do for sustenance?
-Go tend to your errands!

491
00:30:16,916 --> 00:30:19,000
We got him on the line!
Come, Muthammal!

492
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:22,416
PP holding trunk call
from Annamalai University.

493
00:30:22,541 --> 00:30:23,750
"Annamalai?"

494
00:30:23,875 --> 00:30:26,250
(Telugu) Is this an MP's residence
or a post office, mom?

495
00:30:27,375 --> 00:30:29,666
He and Ratna are childhood friends,
right?

496
00:30:29,791 --> 00:30:30,875
Go answer it, Muthammal.

497
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,291
Hello?
-What is it, grandma?

498
00:30:38,416 --> 00:30:40,000
Little one?
-I hear you! Go on!

499
00:30:40,125 --> 00:30:43,250
We can't send money this month to you.
-What happened?

500
00:30:43,375 --> 00:30:45,916
At the post office,
every damn thing is in Hindi!

501
00:30:46,041 --> 00:30:47,041
"Hindi?"

502
00:30:47,166 --> 00:30:51,541
In just one day, these chumps rendered me,
an eighth grade graduate, illiterate!

503
00:30:52,791 --> 00:30:56,125
I'll have your brother send money to you
by train.

504
00:30:56,250 --> 00:30:57,625
What about the other students?

505
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:08,041
Shammi Kapoor is in a league of his own!

506
00:31:11,791 --> 00:31:13,375
Who the hell stopped the screening?

507
00:31:24,875 --> 00:31:27,250
The kid from the engineering department
changed the reel!

508
00:31:27,375 --> 00:31:28,541
Thinks he's a big shot!

509
00:31:28,666 --> 00:31:30,791
Will you play a Hindi film
or do I smash your head?

510
00:31:30,916 --> 00:31:31,916
Hey, monkey!

511
00:31:32,041 --> 00:31:33,500
Hindi films for three weeks in a row?

512
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:35,375
Sit quietly in a corner
and watch our film!

513
00:31:35,500 --> 00:31:37,041
Crackling dialogues right here!

514
00:31:37,541 --> 00:31:38,541
Thrash him!

515
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:41,750
Careful, Durai!

516
00:31:54,125 --> 00:31:55,916
Why are you beating up kids?

517
00:31:56,041 --> 00:31:57,500
We've got bigger fish to fry!
Come!

518
00:31:58,666 --> 00:31:59,666
Come along!

519
00:32:01,625 --> 00:32:05,250
The central minister has decreed the
Hindi Federation as a national institution!

520
00:32:05,375 --> 00:32:07,625
It'll be announced on the radio
at 7 AM tomorrow!

521
00:32:08,041 --> 00:32:09,625
Got it, Chinnadurai?
-Hold on!

522
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:13,625
This is the first step they're taking
to make Hindi our sole official language!

523
00:32:16,416 --> 00:32:18,291
Then, we students
have to land the first blow!

524
00:32:18,416 --> 00:32:22,125
You brought quite a scoop
in your first week on the job, Ratna!

525
00:32:22,666 --> 00:32:23,750
We'll torch it!

526
00:32:23,875 --> 00:32:26,625
'In street after street...'
-Get the stuff! Get all the petrol cans!

527
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:28,625
Don't forget the bottles!
-I have them, buddy!

528
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,041
Buddy!
-Come on!

529
00:32:30,166 --> 00:32:31,791
We'll crank it up...
-Come on!

530
00:32:31,916 --> 00:32:33,250
...and stomp it out!
-You got it!

531
00:32:33,375 --> 00:32:35,750
'Gums that flap needlessly,
will have no teeth for company'

532
00:32:35,875 --> 00:32:37,916
Why'd you come all this way,
Ratna?

533
00:32:38,041 --> 00:32:39,666
One trunk call and we'd have come over!

534
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:41,000
Good thing I showed up!

535
00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:43,916
If I hadn't, that politician’s son
would've rearranged your face!

536
00:32:44,041 --> 00:32:46,250
'I'll be by your side, for sure'

537
00:32:46,375 --> 00:32:49,916
'You may dispatch an army after us,
we'll soldier on with all smiles'

538
00:32:55,500 --> 00:32:57,541
Quick! Muthammal will scold us!
-We're coming!

539
00:32:57,666 --> 00:33:00,000
We're heading to tuition class, Chezhiya!
-Right!

540
00:33:00,125 --> 00:33:01,125
See you!
Study well!

541
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:02,750
Mr. Teacher!

542
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:05,375
You said you'd teach me Hindi.
Where are you off to?

543
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:07,125
The Himalayas!
Want to join me?

544
00:33:07,250 --> 00:33:09,250
Forget Hindi!
You keep driving!

545
00:33:09,375 --> 00:33:11,750
Haven't even started teaching,
and you ask me to forget it?

546
00:33:11,875 --> 00:33:13,000
Not a man of your word, eh?

547
00:33:16,041 --> 00:33:17,416
What about the two rupees I gave?

548
00:33:17,541 --> 00:33:19,875
Reclaim it from the Hindi Federation
if you can!

549
00:33:20,416 --> 00:33:21,875
Take it and put it on your forehead!

550
00:33:22,291 --> 00:33:24,375
Keep driving!
Go!

551
00:33:45,916 --> 00:33:47,125
Stand back!

552
00:33:47,250 --> 00:33:48,541
Back off, I say!

553
00:33:52,291 --> 00:33:53,625
(Let justice prevail)

554
00:34:35,250 --> 00:34:36,250
Hello, sir.

555
00:34:38,166 --> 00:34:39,166
Welcome back, sir.

556
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:43,041
Ensure the reports are sent to the CM.

557
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:46,000
The brilliant KGB trainee!

558
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:49,625
You couldn't stop them from burning down
the train, nor could you catch them!

559
00:34:49,750 --> 00:34:51,291
And yet, they assigned you to this?

560
00:34:54,291 --> 00:34:55,291
Arsonism.

561
00:34:55,416 --> 00:34:58,500
The same method of operation
as the train incident of 1959.

562
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:00,125
Could it be the same perpetrator?

563
00:35:06,500 --> 00:35:08,041
She is the intelligence assistant.

564
00:35:08,166 --> 00:35:09,166
Gauri.
-Sir.

565
00:35:10,625 --> 00:35:12,125
Deputed from the postal service?

566
00:35:12,666 --> 00:35:13,791
Yes, sir.

567
00:35:13,916 --> 00:35:15,750
What's my role at the Intelligence Bureau?

568
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,916
It's to not ask such questions
and do what I say. That's all.

569
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:30,916
For doing a day of work, your husband earns
a wage of five 'annas'.

570
00:35:31,416 --> 00:35:33,750
Don't get me started!

571
00:35:33,875 --> 00:35:35,625
Since when has he gone to work?

572
00:35:36,125 --> 00:35:37,666
Useless fellow!

573
00:35:39,791 --> 00:35:41,125
What Math geniuses!

574
00:35:41,250 --> 00:35:42,750
School's out!
Get going, oldies!

575
00:35:43,666 --> 00:35:46,250
They gave you leave on the day
the PM died. Why didn't you come?

576
00:35:47,666 --> 00:35:48,875
I would've come had you died.

577
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,500
The elder grandson's here, right?

578
00:35:50,625 --> 00:35:53,500
He earns well by being a slave to the
Hindi imposing central government!

579
00:35:53,625 --> 00:35:55,250
Wash your hands and feet!

580
00:35:55,375 --> 00:35:56,625
Sure, talk all high and mighty!

581
00:35:56,750 --> 00:35:59,375
Your father died in the line of duty,
leaving a mountain of debt!

582
00:35:59,500 --> 00:36:02,416
Your brother left his studies
to go shovel coal!

583
00:36:03,375 --> 00:36:06,000
Have you ever seen
his coal-stained hands?

584
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,750
He is our savior, man!

585
00:36:08,875 --> 00:36:11,375
Despite knowing that,
you roam around like a hooligan!

586
00:36:11,500 --> 00:36:13,791
Fine. Our savior's there and so,
we can sustain ourselves.

587
00:36:14,500 --> 00:36:17,125
You're there to cook tasty food.
Don't you need someone to eat?

588
00:36:17,750 --> 00:36:20,166
Come, grandma! Feed me!
I'm hungry!

589
00:36:22,666 --> 00:36:23,666
Come on.

590
00:36:26,125 --> 00:36:27,500
We can barely afford
good food.

591
00:36:28,291 --> 00:36:30,125
And you intend to reform
the country, Durai?

592
00:36:31,125 --> 00:36:32,125
Tamarind stew today too?

593
00:36:32,250 --> 00:36:34,291
Even the great Anna eats tamarind stew!
-Brother!

594
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,000
Hello, brother.

595
00:36:36,791 --> 00:36:38,250
Why'd you burn down the building?

596
00:36:38,375 --> 00:36:40,416
Burned it?
Who? Me?

597
00:36:40,541 --> 00:36:42,291
Which building?
-Drop the act!

598
00:36:42,416 --> 00:36:43,750
My hand!
It hurts!

599
00:36:43,875 --> 00:36:45,125
Let him go!

600
00:36:46,125 --> 00:36:47,416
I've come straight from college!

601
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,291
Definitely her handiwork!
-"Her"?

602
00:36:51,416 --> 00:36:52,416
Who?

603
00:36:52,916 --> 00:36:53,916
Kannagi, grandma!

604
00:36:57,291 --> 00:37:00,500
Her anger won't subside unless she burns
something in Madurai once a year!

605
00:37:00,625 --> 00:37:02,041
She definitely did it!

606
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,750
Trying to be funny?

607
00:37:03,875 --> 00:37:06,500
Be it in blood or in water,
I can recognize your handwriting!

608
00:37:07,250 --> 00:37:08,291
(Let justice prevail)

609
00:37:16,750 --> 00:37:17,750
Stop!

610
00:37:19,250 --> 00:37:22,750
I've been soft with you as you're orphans,
but you're always at each other’s throats!

611
00:37:23,875 --> 00:37:24,916
Stop!

612
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:26,875
Don't!

613
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,250
Careful, O elder one!

614
00:37:28,375 --> 00:37:30,875
'In street after street,
we'll strike back in kind'

615
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:34,750
'If they try beating us down,
we'll finish it, no sweat'

616
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:40,000
'Gums that flap needlessly,
will no longer have teeth for company'

617
00:37:40,125 --> 00:37:44,166
'This khadi-clad army will twist
the system around'

618
00:37:44,291 --> 00:37:45,416
Chinna!

619
00:37:51,041 --> 00:37:54,416
You two have nothing better to do
than fighting?

620
00:37:54,541 --> 00:37:56,416
We're trying to work over here!

621
00:37:56,541 --> 00:37:58,625
Get going, you!
This is always a habit with them!

622
00:37:58,750 --> 00:38:00,541
Why'd you burn that building, you rascal?

623
00:38:00,666 --> 00:38:02,375
Get out of here!
There are people around!

624
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:04,375
They changed everything to Hindi
overnight!

625
00:38:06,375 --> 00:38:08,125
Students didn't get their money orders!

626
00:38:08,250 --> 00:38:11,125
If we don't pay up, they won't feed us
at the mess or let us write exams!

627
00:38:11,541 --> 00:38:13,125
You need to think it through!

628
00:38:14,875 --> 00:38:16,375
The minute they imposed a language...

629
00:38:16,791 --> 00:38:18,625
...notice how we begin struggling
for food?

630
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,250
If we don't question this...

631
00:38:21,375 --> 00:38:24,250
...they won't even spare
the downtrodden!

632
00:38:24,875 --> 00:38:27,375
There are folks in the legislative assembly
to question that!

633
00:38:32,125 --> 00:38:33,125
Not a brick!

634
00:38:35,041 --> 00:38:36,916
Think acts of arson can fix everything?

635
00:38:37,375 --> 00:38:39,625
The public will never endorse
the use of violence!

636
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:42,166
Your only job is to study!
Just focus on that!

637
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:45,916
They won't endorse violence,
but they'll show up to watch it, right?

638
00:38:46,375 --> 00:38:47,416
That's good enough!

639
00:38:47,541 --> 00:38:48,625
Tamil will prevail!

640
00:38:50,375 --> 00:38:51,375
Durai!

641
00:38:53,250 --> 00:38:55,166
You wretches! Always a habit with you!
-Stop!

642
00:38:55,291 --> 00:38:56,625
Stop it!
Why are you doing this?

643
00:38:56,750 --> 00:38:58,166
Stop!
-Listen to me, Durai!

644
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:04,166
At this age, you won't see
my point.

645
00:39:04,666 --> 00:39:06,166
You accomplished your goal, right?

646
00:39:06,291 --> 00:39:08,375
Promise you won't burn or destroy
anything again.

647
00:39:08,500 --> 00:39:10,125
If you're caught, they won't spare you!

648
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,250
Have I ever asked you for anything
before?

649
00:39:17,875 --> 00:39:18,875
Alright, brother.

650
00:39:19,291 --> 00:39:20,666
I won't burn anything anymore.

651
00:39:27,500 --> 00:39:29,541
'Even if the town entire
stands opposite...'

652
00:39:29,666 --> 00:39:32,416
'...I'll be by your side, for sure'

653
00:39:32,541 --> 00:39:36,000
'You may dispatch an army after us,
we'll soldier on with all smiles'

654
00:39:36,416 --> 00:39:38,541
'Even the skies
will shake with thunder'

655
00:39:38,666 --> 00:39:40,041
'So high is our aim'

656
00:39:40,166 --> 00:39:42,500
What the hell?
You gave your word in a heartbeat!

657
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,875
His beatings scared you?

658
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,291
Like that'd scare me!

659
00:39:47,125 --> 00:39:49,791
For the first time in my life,
my brother hugged me.

660
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,375
My precious!

661
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:53,791
You softie!

662
00:39:53,916 --> 00:39:56,041
That Telugu girl next door
is corrupting you!

663
00:39:56,500 --> 00:39:57,500
Let's go.

664
00:40:00,875 --> 00:40:02,666
What, brother?
-Squat, brother!

665
00:40:02,791 --> 00:40:04,375
Come home once a week, without fail!

666
00:40:05,125 --> 00:40:07,375
For what?
To eat Grandma's tamarind stew?

667
00:40:07,500 --> 00:40:08,500
Buzz off!

668
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,625
Lay off the troublemaking!
Listen to this 'anna' (brother), too!

669
00:40:12,375 --> 00:40:15,250
Come on! I swore to you, didn't I?
Then what?

670
00:40:15,750 --> 00:40:16,750
Get on!

671
00:40:17,166 --> 00:40:19,250
Get on, I say!
-Always nitpicking!

672
00:40:19,375 --> 00:40:20,541
Take these inside!

673
00:40:22,500 --> 00:40:23,500
Come here!

674
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:25,500
Go on!

675
00:40:31,416 --> 00:40:35,000
'I shall walk with pride,
knowing my brother is by my side'

676
00:40:35,625 --> 00:40:39,291
'Standing upon your shoulders,
I shall snatch the stars'

677
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:44,000
'The world's in the palm of your hand...
Spin it with style'

678
00:40:44,416 --> 00:40:47,541
'Even when everything rises in opposition,
let your spirit never fade'

679
00:40:47,666 --> 00:40:48,916
Brother...

680
00:40:49,041 --> 00:40:51,375
'We may be poles apart,
but our pride's one'

681
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:53,375
'Let's see this through,
come what may'

682
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:03,541
(Hindi) The train's moving! Get in!
-Okay, sir!

683
00:41:15,875 --> 00:41:17,541
The Chief Minister will see you now, sir.

684
00:41:25,625 --> 00:41:26,625
Good Morning.

685
00:41:29,125 --> 00:41:32,750
Since the year 1939...

686
00:41:34,250 --> 00:41:37,250
...protests against Hindi imposition
have taken place here.

687
00:41:37,875 --> 00:41:41,416
They'll protest for a while
before moving on to other business.

688
00:41:42,125 --> 00:41:45,250
I've seen the same damn schtick
for the last twenty five years!

689
00:41:46,125 --> 00:41:48,750
Now, a bunch of hooligans...

690
00:41:49,375 --> 00:41:51,375
...burned down a building.

691
00:41:52,375 --> 00:41:53,916
Is it really that big an issue?

692
00:41:54,041 --> 00:41:56,416
And you came all the way from Delhi
to investigate it?

693
00:41:56,916 --> 00:42:00,916
You're yet to witness
January 26th, 1965, if I'm right.

694
00:42:01,541 --> 00:42:02,541
That's why I'm here.

695
00:42:05,291 --> 00:42:06,666
"Special Powers Act."

696
00:42:09,791 --> 00:42:13,125
That means you have the right
to do anything you wish?

697
00:42:14,500 --> 00:42:17,875
You have an all-encompassing authority
granted by the Prime Minister, am I right?

698
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,625
Then what are the cops and ministers
here for?

699
00:42:21,875 --> 00:42:23,250
They have an important job, sir.

700
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:28,000
To sign every file
we send over.

701
00:42:32,416 --> 00:42:34,541
(Telugu) 'O little lassie...'

702
00:42:42,125 --> 00:42:43,250
"Ratnamala."

703
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,500
"Apprentice"?

704
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,875
"Trains will run without you.
Even the govt. will run without my father."

705
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:55,375
"Without Ratnamala, the National Radio
will be at a standstill! Understand that!"

706
00:42:55,875 --> 00:42:56,875
Yes, I have.

707
00:42:58,041 --> 00:43:01,375
"The High and Noble MP's daughter
reaches high to clean windows!"

708
00:43:01,500 --> 00:43:03,000
Great headline, isn't it?

709
00:43:04,875 --> 00:43:05,916
How much do you want?

710
00:43:07,875 --> 00:43:11,250
Keep it. You'll need it to buy
cleaning fluids and wash cloths!

711
00:43:13,250 --> 00:43:14,250
Teach me Hindi!

712
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,125
The Hindi Federation can do that!

713
00:43:16,666 --> 00:43:17,875
You burned it down, right?

714
00:43:22,041 --> 00:43:23,625
How can I teach you?
I can't do it!

715
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:24,750
Why not?

716
00:43:25,291 --> 00:43:28,750
I'm the secretary of the All India
Anti-Hindi Students Council!

717
00:43:29,791 --> 00:43:31,750
Does your daddy know about that,
Ms. Secretary?

718
00:43:33,666 --> 00:43:35,625
(Telugu) 'O little lassie...'

719
00:43:43,750 --> 00:43:44,875
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk'

720
00:43:45,541 --> 00:43:48,625
(Telugu) 'The womenfolk have risen'

721
00:43:50,166 --> 00:43:51,166
Hey!

722
00:43:52,875 --> 00:43:53,875
(Telugu) What?

723
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:55,416
5 AM tomorrow!

724
00:43:56,125 --> 00:43:58,625
Not just my father.
Nobody should know about this!

725
00:44:02,500 --> 00:44:04,500
But no fee!
Make note of that as well!

726
00:44:05,375 --> 00:44:06,416
(Telugu) Stingy fellow!

727
00:44:08,500 --> 00:44:09,625
What'd you just say?

728
00:44:10,375 --> 00:44:13,125
Make sure you come by 5:10.
Now go!

729
00:44:18,875 --> 00:44:21,625
(Hindi) A for apple!

730
00:44:22,375 --> 00:44:24,791
(Hindi) B for ball!

731
00:44:25,791 --> 00:44:28,666
(Hindi) A for apple!
-(Hindi) A for apple!

732
00:44:29,125 --> 00:44:30,666
(Hindi) A for...

733
00:44:31,041 --> 00:44:32,125
(Hindi) Apple!

734
00:44:34,541 --> 00:44:35,791
(Hindi) A for...
-Poovai!

735
00:44:35,916 --> 00:44:37,666
Work properly or I'll whack you!
-Got it!

736
00:44:37,791 --> 00:44:38,791
Pay attention!

737
00:44:39,916 --> 00:44:41,375
(Hindi) A for...

738
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:43,500
(Hindi) A for?
-(Hindi) A for...

739
00:44:43,625 --> 00:44:45,500
(Hindi) Apple! Apple! Apple!
-Brother!

740
00:44:45,625 --> 00:44:48,250
She's saying 'A for Apple'!
-I'll rip your tongue out!

741
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,375
Spare me this crap!
-Wait!

742
00:44:51,125 --> 00:44:53,750
If you learn Hindi, you can sell soda
up north! Business will boom!

743
00:44:53,875 --> 00:44:55,875
I don't care if it booms or bombs!

744
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,625
I own this factory!

745
00:44:57,750 --> 00:45:00,625
If anyone sees me getting whacked by her,
I'll even lose local business!

746
00:45:00,750 --> 00:45:01,750
Leave me be!

747
00:45:02,625 --> 00:45:04,291
She'll teach us for no charge!

748
00:45:04,416 --> 00:45:05,875
No one else does that!
-(Hindi) Sit!

749
00:45:08,291 --> 00:45:10,500
You received awards
from greats like Anna and Periyar!

750
00:45:10,625 --> 00:45:13,250
Should you learn Hindi from this sadist
to make a living?

751
00:45:13,375 --> 00:45:14,500
Come on!

752
00:45:15,125 --> 00:45:17,250
Don't you know even Anna learned Hindi,
Vaigarai?

753
00:45:17,375 --> 00:45:18,875
We ought to know what's in it, right?

754
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:21,166
He probably learned from a good teacher!
Buzz off!

755
00:45:21,291 --> 00:45:22,625
A for Apple, eh?
You've had it!

756
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:25,041
Why are you taking it out on me
if you don't get Hindi?

757
00:45:25,166 --> 00:45:26,166
You run along too!

758
00:45:26,291 --> 00:45:28,500
I won't! I'm here to learn!
Continue!

759
00:45:29,375 --> 00:45:32,875
(Broken Hindi) A for Apple!
B for ball!

760
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,625
You may be dumb,
but you have passion.

761
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,541
Good. I like it.

762
00:45:37,666 --> 00:45:39,000
(Broken Hindi) B for ball.

763
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:46,750
That's... from the engine...

764
00:45:48,625 --> 00:45:50,916
If you come to class
like a pile of dirty laundry...

765
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:53,500
...how can you learn properly?

766
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:55,000
Come neat and clean!

767
00:45:55,416 --> 00:45:56,416
Then, we'll continue.

768
00:45:58,291 --> 00:46:00,000
Run along!

769
00:46:01,875 --> 00:46:03,791
That's all? Only two words?
-(Hindi) Go!

770
00:46:03,916 --> 00:46:07,125
At this rate, when will I finish
learning Hindi?

771
00:46:12,375 --> 00:46:14,500
How'd we get these donation boxes?

772
00:46:15,166 --> 00:46:18,625
To get donations for the Hindi resistance,
I had them placed all over Madras State!

773
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:23,125
We even sent receipts after learning
where the money was sent from.

774
00:46:23,250 --> 00:46:26,875
Most donations came from Madras,
Madurai, Coimbatore, Trichy and Cuddalore!

775
00:46:27,541 --> 00:46:30,416
Not just students.
Even citizens donated wholeheartedly!

776
00:46:30,541 --> 00:46:31,875
Pollachi went a step further.

777
00:46:32,666 --> 00:46:34,041
Even cops donated!

778
00:46:34,166 --> 00:46:36,125
Kid!
Mr. New Officer!

779
00:46:36,250 --> 00:46:40,041
Where did those protestors buy petrol
to burn the Hindi Federation building?

780
00:46:40,625 --> 00:46:42,500
Instead of investigating that...

781
00:46:42,625 --> 00:46:44,291
...you're securing more funds for them?

782
00:46:44,916 --> 00:46:46,291
Please do your job, sir!

783
00:46:51,291 --> 00:46:53,041
Know where these were found, sir?

784
00:46:55,625 --> 00:46:59,791
I went to a petrol bunk to get some,
saying I need it for an Anti-Hindi protest.

785
00:46:59,916 --> 00:47:02,000
I said I was going to burn down
your party's office.

786
00:47:02,125 --> 00:47:03,291
No one asked for money.

787
00:47:03,416 --> 00:47:06,375
They gave it for free, and told me
to burn down a few buses and trains too!

788
00:47:06,791 --> 00:47:07,791
Mr. Chief Minister!

789
00:47:08,250 --> 00:47:10,250
Your own people are at war with you.

790
00:47:11,541 --> 00:47:12,750
If you don't pick up arms...

791
00:47:14,250 --> 00:47:15,250
...they'll finish you.

792
00:47:15,375 --> 00:47:16,375
We need to fight back!

793
00:47:16,875 --> 00:47:19,791
Monitor all phone calls, telegrams
and letters.

794
00:47:20,791 --> 00:47:25,125
Heads of postal, telegraph and telephone
departments of the state are here.

795
00:47:25,250 --> 00:47:27,916
Flag any communication
which seems suspicious!

796
00:47:28,041 --> 00:47:32,125
We need to keep a close eye on anyone
who are with the Tamil protestors, yes?

797
00:47:32,750 --> 00:47:33,750
No, no.

798
00:47:33,875 --> 00:47:34,875
Everyone!

799
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:37,875
Our ministers, government officials,
civil servants...

800
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:40,500
Monitor everyone who has a telephone.

801
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:42,750
Then what about the Chief Minister?

802
00:47:44,250 --> 00:47:45,666
Even my residence, kid?

803
00:47:47,500 --> 00:47:49,375
Your residence alone has five telephones.

804
00:47:51,125 --> 00:47:52,541
That's where I intend to start!

805
00:47:54,375 --> 00:47:55,375
Sir?

806
00:47:55,791 --> 00:47:56,791
This is war!

807
00:48:02,416 --> 00:48:04,875
A call from Chidambaram
on the PP call line. Proceed.

808
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:06,041
Hello?
-Hello?

809
00:48:06,166 --> 00:48:08,166
Hello? I hear you, Ratna.
Go ahead.

810
00:48:10,291 --> 00:48:11,916
They've begun searching relentlessly.

811
00:48:13,416 --> 00:48:14,916
Didn't think it'd happen so quickly.

812
00:48:15,041 --> 00:48:16,166
Who? The Madras Police?

813
00:48:16,625 --> 00:48:20,250
No. Some demonic officer who came over
from Delhi to investigate this!

814
00:48:20,875 --> 00:48:22,125
He threatened all of us!

815
00:48:22,916 --> 00:48:26,875
He correctly deduced this news was leaked
by the National Radio!

816
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:28,250
You be on your guard, Ratna.

817
00:48:28,625 --> 00:48:31,375
Let me know if you hear anything else.
Got it?

818
00:48:42,125 --> 00:48:43,416
He's cleaned up nicely!

819
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:46,000
Who was on the phone?

820
00:48:47,625 --> 00:48:48,875
I'm the teacher.

821
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:50,375
I ask the questions here.

822
00:48:50,750 --> 00:48:51,750
Head up.

823
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:42,750
'O precious pearl...'

824
00:49:43,500 --> 00:49:44,750
'O precious pearl...'

825
00:49:45,750 --> 00:49:49,166
'My heart's all a flutter'

826
00:49:49,750 --> 00:49:53,250
'The ailment of love
is at my door'

827
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:55,750
Broke into my house, have you?

828
00:49:56,375 --> 00:49:57,875
Had he seen you...

829
00:49:58,000 --> 00:49:59,916
You old crone!
Today is Ugadi!

830
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:02,291
I've brought sweet custard!

831
00:50:02,750 --> 00:50:04,791
I painstakingly made it myself!

832
00:50:06,250 --> 00:50:07,916
Try it and let me know how it is!

833
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:10,000
Hey!

834
00:50:10,125 --> 00:50:11,500
Careful with my pail!

835
00:50:11,625 --> 00:50:12,875
Little one!

836
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:14,875
Why is the custard
coming all the way to the bed?

837
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:17,625
True, grandma!
I've never heard her talk like this.

838
00:50:18,250 --> 00:50:19,250
Something's not right.

839
00:50:20,041 --> 00:50:21,125
Get that custard!

840
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:37,000
He drank it all!

841
00:50:39,666 --> 00:50:42,125
Grandma! The cow gave birth yesterday,
right?

842
00:50:42,250 --> 00:50:43,791
Yes!
What about it?

843
00:50:44,541 --> 00:50:45,916
Pour the colostrum in that pail!

844
00:50:46,625 --> 00:50:49,791
They'll think ill of us
if we return an empty vessel!

845
00:50:50,416 --> 00:50:53,000
What do we care if they think ill of us?

846
00:50:53,125 --> 00:50:54,250
Come here, you old crone!

847
00:50:54,875 --> 00:50:55,875
What?

848
00:50:56,291 --> 00:50:58,500
You'll have to go there someday
to discuss marriage!

849
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:00,500
Come!

850
00:51:02,375 --> 00:51:04,250
Oh my goodness!

851
00:51:05,750 --> 00:51:07,416
Fine, I'll make some!
Go give it to them!

852
00:51:07,541 --> 00:51:09,125
Why must I give it?

853
00:51:09,250 --> 00:51:11,000
Tell the one who drank the custard
to do it!

854
00:51:11,125 --> 00:51:12,125
Can't you do any chore?

855
00:51:12,250 --> 00:51:13,375
Don't scold him, grandma!

856
00:51:14,791 --> 00:51:15,791
He's an engineer.

857
00:51:16,541 --> 00:51:17,625
I'll go give it.

858
00:51:36,166 --> 00:51:37,500
How'd you figure it out?

859
00:51:38,166 --> 00:51:39,500
Like it's rocket science!

860
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:41,541
She says it's Ugadi
in the wrong month!

861
00:51:41,666 --> 00:51:43,625
He drinks up custard
without brushing his teeth!

862
00:51:43,750 --> 00:51:45,416
Just to go next door,
he takes a bath!

863
00:51:45,541 --> 00:51:47,000
Hurry!
-(Hindi) Is it "She came"?

864
00:51:47,125 --> 00:51:48,250
(Hindi) Or "He came"?

865
00:51:48,750 --> 00:51:50,416
(Hindi) Can a chair mend himself?

866
00:51:50,916 --> 00:51:52,375
Wrong, wrong, wrong, wrong!

867
00:51:53,375 --> 00:51:54,500
How many times do I tell you?

868
00:51:54,916 --> 00:51:57,666
Chair is of feminine gender.
Bed is masculine gender!

869
00:51:58,500 --> 00:52:01,375
Are the chair and bed
looking to have babies together?

870
00:52:01,916 --> 00:52:03,250
Why look at gender there?

871
00:52:04,125 --> 00:52:05,666
Just follow my instructions!

872
00:52:08,250 --> 00:52:09,291
Next one!
Quickly!

873
00:52:10,375 --> 00:52:11,416
I need to leave soon.

874
00:52:13,666 --> 00:52:14,666
For what?

875
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:18,250
A woman has a thousand errands
at any moment!

876
00:52:18,375 --> 00:52:20,000
Should I check with you
before doing them?

877
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:25,041
Understood.

878
00:52:25,166 --> 00:52:27,250
You got some protesting to do
with that damn Durai!

879
00:52:28,125 --> 00:52:29,375
Don't talk about your brother!

880
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:31,625
He's out there fighting valiantly!

881
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:35,250
And look at you!
Moron of the highest order!

882
00:52:36,416 --> 00:52:37,416
(Telugu) Knucklehead!

883
00:52:37,875 --> 00:52:38,875
(Hindi) Scaredy cat!

884
00:52:41,625 --> 00:52:43,125
(Hindi) Scaredy cat, eh?

885
00:52:43,250 --> 00:52:44,375
That means coward, right?

886
00:52:44,875 --> 00:52:45,875
Jeez...
-Right?

887
00:52:46,875 --> 00:52:47,875
(Telugu) O dear God...

888
00:52:48,500 --> 00:52:50,500
(Hindi) Greetings, sir!
Have a good day!

889
00:52:51,375 --> 00:52:52,750
(Hindi) What brings you here?

890
00:52:52,875 --> 00:52:53,875
You said that perfectly!

891
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:55,541
You really are in a royal mess!

892
00:52:56,500 --> 00:52:59,791
Like Rajaji went to learn Hindi
from Mahatma Gandhi's son...

893
00:52:59,916 --> 00:53:02,666
...this Member of Parliament's daughter
is the best you could find?

894
00:53:04,916 --> 00:53:06,125
Sure, let's go with that!

895
00:53:08,125 --> 00:53:09,500
Something funny?

896
00:53:09,625 --> 00:53:13,000
Rajaji ended up not learning
even a single word of Hindi!

897
00:53:14,375 --> 00:53:17,750
Then what was Gandhi's son doing
instead of teaching him Hindi?

898
00:53:17,875 --> 00:53:19,500
Hindi, Schmindi!

899
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:22,416
He wooed Rajaji's daughter
and married her!

900
00:53:23,125 --> 00:53:24,250
I see...
-Chezhiya!

901
00:53:24,375 --> 00:53:25,875
Heard you're getting married too!

902
00:53:26,375 --> 00:53:29,375
Your grandmother seems to be scouring
the town for a Hindi speaking girl...

903
00:53:29,500 --> 00:53:31,916
...as you're about to land a job in Delhi!

904
00:53:32,041 --> 00:53:33,416
She asked me about it too.

905
00:53:34,875 --> 00:53:35,875
Sir!

906
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:37,500
Let me know if you know any good girls!

907
00:53:42,291 --> 00:53:44,875
Can't say one word in Hindi,
and she wants a Hindi girl for him?

908
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:47,041
Ratnamala!
-That old crone wants the moon!

909
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:50,291
Stop, big shot!
-(Telugu) At this rate...

910
00:53:50,416 --> 00:53:52,416
