01:00:15,500 --> 01:00:16,500
Keep the change.

996
01:00:24,125 --> 01:00:26,541
You dare try to burn down
the constitution?

997
01:00:27,000 --> 01:00:28,625
Call it baptism by fire!

998
01:00:28,750 --> 01:00:32,625
As January 26th marks Republic Day...

999
01:00:33,500 --> 01:00:36,125
If the police don't permit us
to raise black flags that day...

1000
01:00:37,375 --> 01:00:39,750
...I suggest we raise black flags
in our own homes!

1001
01:00:40,250 --> 01:00:41,750
Comrades!
-You're under arrest, sir!

1002
01:00:41,875 --> 01:00:43,416
I urge you all to do so!
-For treason!

1003
01:00:43,541 --> 01:00:45,375
You can shut down this press.

1004
01:00:45,875 --> 01:00:48,375
The same story is being printed
in thirteen presses!

1005
01:00:48,791 --> 01:00:51,166
How will you shut that down, son?

1006
01:00:52,291 --> 01:00:54,750
When the sun rises,
the drums will roar, for sure!

1007
01:00:57,666 --> 01:00:58,666
Now!

1008
01:01:04,250 --> 01:01:05,500
It's okay!
I'll handle this.

1009
01:01:05,625 --> 01:01:07,875
I'll handle it! Travel safe!
-Come peacefully, sir!

1010
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:09,000
Shall we go?

1011
01:01:09,500 --> 01:01:11,541
This arrest shouldn't be
on any official record.

1012
01:01:11,666 --> 01:01:14,000
Yes, sir.
-Keep moving him.

1013
01:01:14,125 --> 01:01:17,125
Four days later,
throw him into the Palayamkottai Jail.

1014
01:01:18,541 --> 01:01:21,500
You're going for your interview
after paying Chinna's college fees?

1015
01:01:22,375 --> 01:01:23,541
Make sure you pray.

1016
01:01:24,791 --> 01:01:28,041
O dear Gods, please band together
and be by my grandson's side.

1017
01:01:28,166 --> 01:01:29,500
Take good care of him!

1018
01:01:30,666 --> 01:01:32,750
When you come back,
it will be with a job!

1019
01:01:33,500 --> 01:01:34,666
You think so?

1020
01:01:34,791 --> 01:01:37,750
If they could arrest our leader overnight,
think what they'll do to us!

1021
01:01:37,875 --> 01:01:39,416
So what if we have no leader?

1022
01:01:39,541 --> 01:01:40,541
We'll do it ourselves!

1023
01:01:40,666 --> 01:01:43,000
At the party office entrance
in Maasi Street, Madurai!

1024
01:01:43,125 --> 01:01:46,625
No matter who gets in the way,
we burn their party flag right there!

1025
01:01:47,250 --> 01:01:49,791
Who will burn it?
We asked across the entire district!

1026
01:01:49,916 --> 01:01:50,916
No one wants to do it!

1027
01:01:51,375 --> 01:01:52,375
I'll burn it.

1028
01:01:53,041 --> 01:01:54,750
They'll arrest you for treason!

1029
01:01:54,875 --> 01:01:56,500
They'll target and destroy
your family!

1030
01:01:56,916 --> 01:01:58,916
A few years ago, the Puranaanooru Squad...

1031
01:01:59,041 --> 01:02:01,500
...burned down a train
and rolled back Hindi imposition!

1032
01:02:01,625 --> 01:02:02,666
We're just like them!

1033
01:02:03,125 --> 01:02:04,125
I say we proceed!

1034
01:02:04,250 --> 01:02:05,666
Even if I die,
I die a warrior!

1035
01:02:05,791 --> 01:02:07,291
All hail Warrior Chinnadurai!

1036
01:02:07,416 --> 01:02:09,666
All hail Warrior Chinnadurai!
-Hey!

1037
01:02:09,791 --> 01:02:11,750
Who are you guys?
What's happening here?

1038
01:02:11,875 --> 01:02:14,500
"Who are we"? Members of
Madurai's Anti-Hindi imposition squad!

1039
01:02:14,625 --> 01:02:15,791
Who the hell are you?

1040
01:02:16,875 --> 01:02:20,250
Your precious comrade who's all
'consequences be damned' over there?

1041
01:02:21,125 --> 01:02:22,416
His big brother!

1042
01:02:22,541 --> 01:02:24,416
Please understand
what we're fighting for...

1043
01:02:24,541 --> 01:02:26,416
Don't get in the middle
of our family issue. Go!

1044
01:02:27,250 --> 01:02:28,625
Fine, beat yourselves to death!

1045
01:02:29,750 --> 01:02:30,875
What's with you, sir?

1046
01:02:31,000 --> 01:02:34,625
You have a home, get meals on time,
good clothes and money whenever you want!

1047
01:02:34,750 --> 01:02:36,625
So, you feel privileged enough to protest!

1048
01:02:37,500 --> 01:02:40,125
Know how much these kids' parents struggle
to educate them?

1049
01:02:40,250 --> 01:02:41,375
Considered their future?

1050
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:46,666
Expect us to learn Hindi
and become sycophants like you?

1051
01:02:48,041 --> 01:02:49,666
That's my fate.

1052
01:02:50,041 --> 01:02:51,250
You just focus on studying!

1053
01:02:53,500 --> 01:02:55,166
No one here can get a job!

1054
01:02:55,291 --> 01:02:57,375
Then why do we need to pay college fees?

1055
01:03:01,500 --> 01:03:02,875
Why'd you rip the demand draft?

1056
01:03:03,375 --> 01:03:05,375
Stop it, brother!
-Why'd you rip it?

1057
01:03:05,500 --> 01:03:07,041
Don't you know the value of education?

1058
01:03:07,166 --> 01:03:08,291
Brother!

1059
01:03:08,875 --> 01:03:09,875
Durai!

1060
01:03:12,000 --> 01:03:14,041
No, brother!
Don't do it!

1061
01:03:15,375 --> 01:03:16,375
Durai!
-Don't!

1062
01:03:16,916 --> 01:03:17,916
Don't fight!

1063
01:03:19,541 --> 01:03:21,000
You call yourself a leader?

1064
01:03:22,125 --> 01:03:23,875
Did you bloody think about your followers?

1065
01:03:24,000 --> 01:03:25,000
No, brother!

1066
01:03:25,125 --> 01:03:27,250
Let's see how you protest!
-Don't do it, brother!

1067
01:03:28,750 --> 01:03:31,125
I'd rather see you be crippled
than lie dead in the street!

1068
01:03:32,125 --> 01:03:33,125
Durai!

1069
01:03:35,125 --> 01:03:36,500
Your leader's leg is broken!

1070
01:03:36,625 --> 01:03:39,000
He must be bedridden for 45 days!
All protests cancelled!

1071
01:03:40,666 --> 01:03:43,000
I'll head straight to Maasi Street
after my interview!

1072
01:03:43,125 --> 01:03:44,500
If I see any of you there...

1073
01:03:45,375 --> 01:03:47,166
...I'll bury you all where you stand!

1074
01:03:47,750 --> 01:03:49,625
Just eat and only focus on studying!

1075
01:03:50,875 --> 01:03:51,875
Eat!

1076
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:55,625
Give me a hand!
-Get him to the hospital!

1077
01:03:55,750 --> 01:03:58,750
Let's get him to the hospital!
-Go easy on his leg!

1078
01:03:58,875 --> 01:04:00,875
Hurry! Come on!
-Lift him up!

1079
01:04:09,541 --> 01:04:10,791
Can't you watch your step?

1080
01:04:11,541 --> 01:04:13,625
Hey! Don't fall on the tracks!
-My pen, brother!

1081
01:04:13,750 --> 01:04:15,041
Buy another one!

1082
01:04:15,500 --> 01:04:16,625
I don't have money for that.

1083
01:04:16,750 --> 01:04:19,000
I only have enough
for a return ticket after my exam!

1084
01:04:26,041 --> 01:04:27,250
What exam, Ayyakannu?

1085
01:04:28,625 --> 01:04:30,375
The Union Public Service Commission exam.

1086
01:04:30,500 --> 01:04:31,791
This is my first trip to Madras!

1087
01:04:32,666 --> 01:04:34,291
Didn't know the route,
and got lost!

1088
01:04:34,750 --> 01:04:36,875
I'm running late!
This is my last shot!

1089
01:04:37,916 --> 01:04:40,250
The stress makes me feel
I forgot everything I studied!

1090
01:04:43,000 --> 01:04:44,041
Here!

1091
01:04:44,166 --> 01:04:45,541
This is a very lucky pen!

1092
01:04:45,666 --> 01:04:47,000
The great Anna gifted it to me!

1093
01:04:47,125 --> 01:04:48,291
Do well!

1094
01:04:51,416 --> 01:04:52,750
Brother!

1095
01:04:53,125 --> 01:04:54,625
Brother!

1096
01:04:56,166 --> 01:04:58,500
Thanks! I'll return it in the evening!
-You better!

1097
01:04:58,625 --> 01:05:01,000
Don't drop it on the tracks!
-I'll definitely return it!

1098
01:05:01,125 --> 01:05:03,250
I'll be the first collector
from my town! Just watch!

1099
01:05:05,875 --> 01:05:06,875
When do you head back?

1100
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:09,000
I take the evening Boat Mail Express
once I'm done.

1101
01:05:09,125 --> 01:05:10,291
Very well.

1102
01:05:10,416 --> 01:05:11,500
What about your pen?

1103
01:05:12,291 --> 01:05:13,791
I'll leave it at this counter
at 4 PM!

1104
01:05:14,416 --> 01:05:16,166
You better keep it, okay?
-I will, brother!

1105
01:05:16,791 --> 01:05:18,750
Come! Get on this bus
and get off at Panagal Park!

1106
01:05:18,875 --> 01:05:20,375
Your exam center will be close by!

1107
01:05:20,500 --> 01:05:22,125
Hurry!
-Thank you very much, brother!

1108
01:05:26,791 --> 01:05:29,375
Those who are elder must be addressed
as 'aap' (you honorific).

1109
01:05:30,250 --> 01:05:32,375
And those younger
must be addressed as 'tum' (you).

1110
01:05:33,500 --> 01:05:35,125
And it's 'ithar aoongi'
(I'll be there).

1111
01:05:36,250 --> 01:05:38,000
No, you're mistaken.

1112
01:05:38,125 --> 01:05:39,875
As you're a male,
it should be...

1113
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:42,541
...it should be 'aoonga'.
My mistake, sir.

1114
01:05:42,666 --> 01:05:43,666
I'll correct it, sir.

1115
01:05:44,875 --> 01:05:46,291
Sorry. You are not eligible.

1116
01:05:47,875 --> 01:05:48,875
Sir...

1117
01:05:49,375 --> 01:05:50,625
Why, sir?

1118
01:05:50,750 --> 01:05:53,250
Didn't I answer correctly
in the job-related questions?

1119
01:05:53,875 --> 01:05:55,375
Your Hindi is very weak.

1120
01:05:55,916 --> 01:05:59,250
The other candidates...
Nikhil, Amit, and Keshav...

1121
01:05:59,375 --> 01:06:02,750
They've scored very well
in the written and oral Hindi tests.

1122
01:06:02,875 --> 01:06:04,000
You are unemployable.

1123
01:06:04,125 --> 01:06:05,625
Mr. Che... Chezeeyan.

1124
01:06:06,125 --> 01:06:07,125
Better luck next time.

1125
01:06:08,416 --> 01:06:09,416
Sir...

1126
01:06:10,500 --> 01:06:11,500
Sir...

1127
01:06:11,625 --> 01:06:12,791
I swear I don't get it.

1128
01:06:13,791 --> 01:06:16,041
You said knowing Hindi was good enough
to land this job.

1129
01:06:16,166 --> 01:06:18,166
But now, you expect me
to speak fluently like them?

1130
01:06:18,291 --> 01:06:19,291
How is this fair?

1131
01:06:20,041 --> 01:06:21,625
They've been speaking it
since birth.

1132
01:06:21,750 --> 01:06:23,500
I've only been learning
for a little while.

1133
01:06:23,625 --> 01:06:25,125
There's bound to be a difference, yes?

1134
01:06:27,375 --> 01:06:29,500
Even you couldn't pronounce my name
properly.

1135
01:06:29,625 --> 01:06:31,625
Does it mean you're unemployable?
No, right?

1136
01:06:32,125 --> 01:06:34,625
I put in a lot of effort for six months
to learn this language.

1137
01:06:35,250 --> 01:06:36,625
I'll pick it up on the job, sir.

1138
01:06:37,041 --> 01:06:39,000
I speak English well, sir.

1139
01:06:39,125 --> 01:06:40,125
So what?

1140
01:06:40,250 --> 01:06:42,541
We've even asked
the English-speaking President...

1141
01:06:42,666 --> 01:06:44,375
...to address the Parliament
in Hindi.

1142
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:45,625
You should change too!

1143
01:06:45,750 --> 01:06:49,666
Mister! Per the Official Languages Act,
it's compulsory to learn Hindi fluently!

1144
01:06:49,791 --> 01:06:53,625
From the Supreme Court to Civil Service
exams, everything will be in Hindi.

1145
01:06:54,041 --> 01:06:55,166
Within one year...

1146
01:06:55,291 --> 01:06:58,916
...the nameboards of every bus stand,
railway station in South India...

1147
01:06:59,041 --> 01:07:00,500
...will be written in Hindi.

1148
01:07:00,625 --> 01:07:02,875
Instead of giving excuses...

1149
01:07:03,000 --> 01:07:05,125
...learn Hindi fluently
and try again. We'll see.

1150
01:07:05,250 --> 01:07:06,875
Mr. Chay-Zhee-An.

1151
01:07:07,875 --> 01:07:08,875
Next!
-Sir...

1152
01:07:09,291 --> 01:07:11,375
No, sir...
I can do it better.

1153
01:07:11,500 --> 01:07:13,500
Give me just one chance.
I'll learn it, sir.

1154
01:07:13,625 --> 01:07:14,916
Next!
-One chance...

1155
01:07:38,375 --> 01:07:42,750
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1156
01:07:42,875 --> 01:07:47,166
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1157
01:07:47,291 --> 01:07:50,291
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1158
01:07:50,416 --> 01:07:54,500
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1159
01:07:54,625 --> 01:07:56,000
Sir!
-Hold it right there!

1160
01:07:56,125 --> 01:07:57,875
Sir!
-Stop him!

1161
01:07:58,000 --> 01:07:59,000
Sir!

1162
01:07:59,125 --> 01:08:00,166
Hey! Get up!
-Sir!

1163
01:08:00,291 --> 01:08:01,500
Sir!
-Get up!

1164
01:08:01,625 --> 01:08:03,375
I came to take my last crack
at the IAS exam.

1165
01:08:03,500 --> 01:08:05,750
They had postponed it by two months,
sent us all home...

1166
01:08:05,875 --> 01:08:07,875
...and said the exam would be conducted
in Hindi!

1167
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:09,000
Son...

1168
01:08:09,125 --> 01:08:13,250
The National Language Committee is yet
to decide if English can be added...

1169
01:08:13,375 --> 01:08:15,875
...along with Hindi as the medium
for IAS exams.

1170
01:08:16,750 --> 01:08:19,541
Please wait until it is publicly announced,
son.

1171
01:08:19,666 --> 01:08:20,875
Don't be hasty.

1172
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:23,750
What if the committee says the exam
will only be in Hindi?

1173
01:08:23,875 --> 01:08:26,875
So what?
You can still write the exam in English!

1174
01:08:30,125 --> 01:08:33,666
They've announced that
you can get a job in the quota system.

1175
01:08:34,125 --> 01:08:36,000
We studied in the Tamil medium, sir.

1176
01:08:36,125 --> 01:08:38,125
It took us 200 years to learn English!

1177
01:08:38,250 --> 01:08:41,291
Who knows how long it will take
to learn yet another language?

1178
01:08:41,416 --> 01:08:43,166
We think in Tamil and write in English.

1179
01:08:43,291 --> 01:08:45,500
We have to check
for spelling mistakes ten times over!

1180
01:08:45,625 --> 01:08:48,375
But Hindi speakers? It's easy,
as it's their mother tongue.

1181
01:08:48,500 --> 01:08:50,250
They're rigging everything
in their favor!

1182
01:08:50,375 --> 01:08:52,625
Shouldn't you speak for us
as our representative, sir?

1183
01:08:52,750 --> 01:08:55,541
I beg of you, sir.
Do not forsake us!

1184
01:08:55,666 --> 01:08:57,750
Toss this lunatic out!
-Do not forsake us, sir!

1185
01:08:58,125 --> 01:09:00,375
Get up! Let's get going!
-Sir!

1186
01:09:00,500 --> 01:09:01,500
Sir!

1187
01:09:01,625 --> 01:09:03,625
Come on!
-I'm not a lunatic, sir!

1188
01:09:04,500 --> 01:09:06,250
Please hear me out, sir!

1189
01:09:13,500 --> 01:09:15,416
Poor lad!

1190
01:09:55,791 --> 01:09:58,500
"Hindi imposition burnt down
the only dream I had."

1191
01:09:58,625 --> 01:10:01,916
"Your language politics
burnt down my future."

1192
01:10:02,041 --> 01:10:04,625
"Your arrogant power
burnt down my life."

1193
01:10:04,750 --> 01:10:08,125
"The useless shell that's left behind?
I shall burn it myself!"

1194
01:10:09,250 --> 01:10:11,750
"Yours truly,
R. Ayyakannu."

1195
01:10:32,625 --> 01:10:34,875
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1196
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:36,750
Move aside!
-Long Live the Chief Minister!

1197
01:10:36,875 --> 01:10:38,125
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1198
01:10:38,541 --> 01:10:39,541
Where is your chief?

1199
01:10:40,625 --> 01:10:43,625
The Chief Minister said
Madras must remain quiet.

1200
01:10:44,166 --> 01:10:46,416
Our chief is on his way
after enforcing that.

1201
01:10:47,125 --> 01:10:48,291
(Madurai - 7 Kilometres)

1202
01:10:49,750 --> 01:10:50,750
Step on it!

1203
01:10:52,500 --> 01:10:54,375
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1204
01:10:54,500 --> 01:10:56,791
(Telugu) Please turn that frown
upside down, dear.

1205
01:10:56,916 --> 01:11:00,791
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1206
01:11:00,916 --> 01:11:04,291
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1207
01:11:05,166 --> 01:11:07,250
It's just students who are protesting,
right?

1208
01:11:07,750 --> 01:11:09,750
Why not let them, sir?
Aren't you a Tamilian, too?

1209
01:11:10,166 --> 01:11:11,166
Pull over.

1210
01:11:11,791 --> 01:11:12,791
Sir?

1211
01:11:14,250 --> 01:11:15,416
I said so in Tamil, didn't I?

1212
01:11:16,000 --> 01:11:17,166
Pull over.
-Sir...

1213
01:11:18,375 --> 01:11:19,375
Yes, sir.

1214
01:11:26,000 --> 01:11:28,166
Sir? Sir!
No, sir!

1215
01:11:28,291 --> 01:11:29,625
Sir!

1216
01:11:33,000 --> 01:11:36,541
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1217
01:11:36,666 --> 01:11:41,625
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1218
01:11:41,750 --> 01:11:45,916
They've shut factories for ink and dyeing
as well as textile mills in Madurai, buddy!

1219
01:11:46,041 --> 01:11:47,625
We don't have black cloth, paper or ink!

1220
01:11:47,750 --> 01:11:48,875
How do we protest now?

1221
01:11:49,000 --> 01:11:51,500
We're surrounded by cops!
Let's leave!

1222
01:11:51,625 --> 01:11:52,625
Come here, child.

1223
01:11:56,125 --> 01:11:57,125
Black...

1224
01:11:58,791 --> 01:11:59,791
Get lost!

1225
01:12:01,375 --> 01:12:04,916
Everyone will take notice of
the black flags that fly in the sky today.

1226
01:12:05,875 --> 01:12:07,541
At ease!

1227
01:12:07,666 --> 01:12:12,000
Do you know why I came to Madurai
to inaugurate Hindi Week?

1228
01:12:12,750 --> 01:12:16,250
I believe the very Madurai where
the Sangam movement propagated Tamil...

1229
01:12:16,375 --> 01:12:20,666
...will also propagate Hindi
which will unite our country!

1230
01:12:21,541 --> 01:12:22,916
At ease!

1231
01:12:26,541 --> 01:12:30,375
From now, the official language of India
is no longer English!

1232
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:35,666
To enforce that, I rechristen
the Indian Gazette to 'Bharat Rajpatra'.

1233
01:12:35,791 --> 01:12:38,875
Under that name,
I release its inaugural Hindi edition!

1234
01:12:39,875 --> 01:12:40,875
Praise be to India!

1235
01:12:42,125 --> 01:12:43,500
(Hindi) The Hindi Week begins!

1236
01:12:43,625 --> 01:12:46,500
(Hindi) The Hindi Week begins!

1237
01:12:46,625 --> 01:12:48,250
(Hindi) The Hindi Week begins!

1238
01:12:48,375 --> 01:12:51,000
Long Live the Chief Minister!

1239
01:12:51,791 --> 01:12:54,375
I saw a gang of students
break into the bank, sir!

1240
01:12:55,500 --> 01:12:56,875
Let them be trapped in there.

