01:30:21,375 --> 01:30:23,541
Law must prevail
and curb their arrogance!

1490
01:30:23,666 --> 01:30:24,750
Long Live Tamil!

1491
01:30:24,875 --> 01:30:27,000
Long Live Tamil!
-Victory to Tamilians!

1492
01:30:27,125 --> 01:30:29,375
These people permitted
a mourning procession.

1493
01:30:29,500 --> 01:30:31,125
But they also invoked Section 144.

1494
01:30:31,250 --> 01:30:34,125
Who's insane? Them or those of us
who work for them? I have no idea!

1495
01:30:37,875 --> 01:30:39,541
"But they also invoked Section 144."

1496
01:30:45,166 --> 01:30:47,125
Everyone leave!
Students are going to riot!

1497
01:30:47,250 --> 01:30:50,166
Close the shops!
Everyone leave!

1498
01:30:50,291 --> 01:30:53,666
We will keep fighting!
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1499
01:30:53,791 --> 01:30:57,250
We will keep fighting!
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1500
01:30:57,375 --> 01:31:00,250
We will keep fighting!
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1501
01:31:00,750 --> 01:31:03,291
Long Live Tamil!

1502
01:31:04,541 --> 01:31:07,416
If your issue is with the government,
go to Delhi and protest!

1503
01:31:07,541 --> 01:31:09,750
Did Gandhi do the Salt Satyagraha Movement
in London?

1504
01:31:10,125 --> 01:31:11,500
Is Delhi the only part of India?

1505
01:31:11,625 --> 01:31:13,125
Is Chidambaram in China?

1506
01:31:15,166 --> 01:31:17,666
Long Live The Republic!
Long Live India!

1507
01:31:17,791 --> 01:31:19,000
Long Live India!

1508
01:31:19,125 --> 01:31:20,625
Long Live Tamil!
-Palaniappan?

1509
01:31:20,750 --> 01:31:21,750
Sir?

1510
01:31:21,875 --> 01:31:23,250
Long Live Tamil!
-Let them pass.

1511
01:31:23,375 --> 01:31:24,375
Sir?

1512
01:31:24,500 --> 01:31:25,625
Let them pass, I say.

1513
01:31:25,750 --> 01:31:27,416
Long Live The Republic!
-Yes, sir.

1514
01:31:27,541 --> 01:31:28,666
Open it up! Let them pass!

1515
01:31:29,625 --> 01:31:30,791
Long Live Tamil!

1516
01:31:40,375 --> 01:31:43,375
We will keep fighting!
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1517
01:31:43,500 --> 01:31:46,375
We will keep fighting!
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1518
01:31:49,500 --> 01:31:50,500
Brother!
-Brother!

1519
01:31:50,625 --> 01:31:51,750
They already left!

1520
01:31:51,875 --> 01:31:53,000
Durai left with them!
-Yes!

1521
01:31:53,125 --> 01:31:54,875
We tried to stop him,
but he didn't listen!

1522
01:31:58,500 --> 01:31:59,916
Brother!

1523
01:32:00,041 --> 01:32:01,250
None of you come along!

1524
01:32:01,375 --> 01:32:03,375
Stay here!
-Listen, brother!

1525
01:32:03,500 --> 01:32:06,666
Do not impose!
Do not impose Hindi!

1526
01:32:06,791 --> 01:32:09,625
Do not snatch away the rights
of Tamilians!

1527
01:32:09,750 --> 01:32:11,166
We will keep fighting!

1528
01:32:11,291 --> 01:32:13,291
We will keep fighting for Tamil!
-Hurry!

1529
01:32:13,416 --> 01:32:14,500
Lock the gate!

1530
01:32:14,625 --> 01:32:17,416
Do not snatch away the rights
of Tamilians!

1531
01:32:17,541 --> 01:32:18,666
Close it quickly!

1532
01:32:18,791 --> 01:32:20,375
We will keep fighting!
-Hold them off!

1533
01:32:20,500 --> 01:32:21,791
We will keep fighting for Tamil!

1534
01:32:21,916 --> 01:32:24,250
Do not impose Hindi!

1535
01:32:24,375 --> 01:32:25,875
Do not snatch away our rights!

1536
01:32:26,000 --> 01:32:27,875
The procession is going along peacefully,
sir.

1537
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:29,291
He's coming peacefully, too.

1538
01:32:29,750 --> 01:32:31,125
Are you sure he's our target?

1539
01:32:31,666 --> 01:32:33,250
He most definitely is not.

1540
01:32:34,250 --> 01:32:35,291
Load this.

1541
01:32:35,416 --> 01:32:36,416
Shoot him in the chest.

1542
01:32:36,875 --> 01:32:37,875
Sir...

1543
01:32:38,000 --> 01:32:39,416
This isn't a rubber bullet.

1544
01:32:39,541 --> 01:32:41,375
It's .303 caliber high velocity bullets!

1545
01:32:41,500 --> 01:32:42,500
It'll kill him!

1546
01:32:43,250 --> 01:32:45,000
We're not sure that he's our target, right?

1547
01:32:46,625 --> 01:32:48,750
You let the one we're after
slip away at Maasi Street.

1548
01:32:49,750 --> 01:32:51,416
If we nab and question him,
he'll talk!

1549
01:32:51,541 --> 01:32:53,166
Shooting him might cause a huge riot!

1550
01:32:54,125 --> 01:32:55,875
Not at all.
He'll never talk.

1551
01:32:56,625 --> 01:32:59,416
Even the last remaining student here
won't rat that man out.

1552
01:33:02,250 --> 01:33:03,375
Mr. Superintendent!

1553
01:33:03,500 --> 01:33:08,916
Know how 150,000 Britishers ruled over
millions of Indians for 200 years?

1554
01:33:10,750 --> 01:33:12,000
They'd only shoot once.

1555
01:33:12,875 --> 01:33:15,875
But the sound of that bullet
would be heard by ten million people!

1556
01:33:16,916 --> 01:33:17,916
This is just like that.

1557
01:33:18,625 --> 01:33:21,000
One outcome?
Another person like him won't rise up.

1558
01:33:21,750 --> 01:33:24,541
The other?
The sound will draw him out!

1559
01:33:29,125 --> 01:33:30,250
We'll keep fighting!

1560
01:33:30,375 --> 01:33:32,791
We'll keep fighting for Tamil!

1561
01:33:32,916 --> 01:33:33,916
Durai!

1562
01:33:34,041 --> 01:33:35,416
There are snipers in position!

1563
01:33:37,166 --> 01:33:38,541
Just rubber bullets!

1564
01:33:38,666 --> 01:33:40,000
They can't fire actual bullets!

1565
01:33:42,375 --> 01:33:43,625
Deploy tear gas.

1566
01:33:46,666 --> 01:33:47,750
Fire.

1567
01:33:47,875 --> 01:33:49,250
Fire!
-We will keep fighting!

1568
01:34:08,250 --> 01:34:09,750
Won't listen, eh?
Still protesting?

1569
01:34:09,875 --> 01:34:11,000
We'll keep fighting!

1570
01:35:05,541 --> 01:35:06,750
Leave!

1571
01:35:06,875 --> 01:35:08,000
Trying to spook us?

1572
01:35:09,375 --> 01:35:10,375
Long Live Tamil!

1573
01:35:38,791 --> 01:35:39,791
Don't fire!

1574
01:35:43,875 --> 01:35:44,875
Fire!

1575
01:35:45,000 --> 01:35:46,416
Long Live Tamil!
-Don't fire!

1576
01:35:46,541 --> 01:35:47,541
Victory to Tam...

1577
01:36:01,750 --> 01:36:08,250
'As the fragrance in the wind,
I'll stand strong'

1578
01:36:12,666 --> 01:36:18,750
'As the fire in my brother's words,
I'll be reborn'

1579
01:36:19,625 --> 01:36:20,625
Don't fire!

1580
01:36:22,125 --> 01:36:23,125
Don't fire!

1581
01:36:25,625 --> 01:36:26,875
Chinna!

1582
01:36:27,000 --> 01:36:29,666
'I'll brave everything...'

1583
01:36:29,791 --> 01:36:33,541
'...for my brother's beside me'

1584
01:36:33,666 --> 01:36:36,916
Chinna?
-'Let the breeze in my breath...'

1585
01:36:37,041 --> 01:36:41,000
'...speak my brother's name'

1586
01:36:41,791 --> 01:36:47,666
'I shall walk with pride,
knowing my brother is by my side'

1587
01:36:51,541 --> 01:36:52,750
You'll be okay!

1588
01:36:52,875 --> 01:36:55,416
'Standing upon his shoulders...'

1589
01:36:55,541 --> 01:36:58,541
Let's go!
-'...I shall snatch the stars'

1590
01:37:07,625 --> 01:37:08,625
Move!

1591
01:37:08,750 --> 01:37:09,875
Don't panic, brother.

1592
01:37:10,000 --> 01:37:12,416
Such a puny bullet can't hurt me!

1593
01:37:12,541 --> 01:37:14,000
Don't say anything!

1594
01:37:25,125 --> 01:37:26,125
Chinna?

1595
01:37:26,750 --> 01:37:28,166
Chinna!

1596
01:37:29,750 --> 01:37:33,541
Chinna...
-'You showed me the world'

1597
01:37:33,666 --> 01:37:37,125
'I was born to be your shadow'

1598
01:37:38,500 --> 01:37:41,166
Chinna?
Look at me!

1599
01:37:41,291 --> 01:37:44,666
'Let's get the fireworks going'

1600
01:37:44,791 --> 01:37:46,500
'Let's twirl our moustaches'

1601
01:37:46,625 --> 01:37:47,666
Don't give up, brother.

1602
01:37:50,125 --> 01:37:51,125
You'll be okay!

1603
01:37:51,250 --> 01:37:52,250
Get up!

1604
01:37:52,375 --> 01:37:54,666
'You are...'

1605
01:37:54,791 --> 01:37:59,041
Stop!
-'You are, you are God's witness'

1606
01:38:09,000 --> 01:38:10,000
Sir?

1607
01:38:10,125 --> 01:38:11,250
Puranaanooru!

1608
01:38:12,291 --> 01:38:14,125
My younger brother, sir!

1609
01:38:15,166 --> 01:38:16,166
Sir...

1610
01:38:16,291 --> 01:38:18,000
Let go of me!

1611
01:38:18,875 --> 01:38:20,250
Let go of me, I say!

1612
01:38:20,375 --> 01:38:21,375
Sir!

1613
01:38:21,500 --> 01:38:23,000
I'm coming, Chinna!

1614
01:38:23,125 --> 01:38:25,375
He's innocent, sir! Please spare him!
Chinna!

1615
01:38:25,500 --> 01:38:27,000
Don't be scared!
I'm coming!

1616
01:38:27,125 --> 01:38:29,500
He's innocent, sir!
Please spare him!

1617
01:38:29,625 --> 01:38:31,666
I'm coming, Chinna!

1618
01:38:33,500 --> 01:38:34,500
He's still alive, sir!

1619
01:38:34,625 --> 01:38:36,291
If we get him to a hospital,
we can save him!

1620
01:38:37,125 --> 01:38:38,250
Get him inside!

1621
01:38:39,875 --> 01:38:40,875
'I'll brave everything'

1622
01:38:41,000 --> 01:38:42,875
By saving him...
-'For my brother's beside me'

1623
01:38:43,000 --> 01:38:44,791
...you expect to win
an award for Best Nurse?

1624
01:38:46,625 --> 01:38:49,291
Let him go!
-'Let the breeze in my breath...'

1625
01:38:49,416 --> 01:38:52,875
He's innocent!
-'...speak my brother's name'

1626
01:38:54,416 --> 01:38:59,916
'I shall walk with pride,
knowing my brother is by my side'

1627
01:39:02,250 --> 01:39:03,750
Let him go straight to the morgue!

1628
01:39:05,416 --> 01:39:11,000
'Standing upon his shoulders,
I shall snatch the stars'

1629
01:39:20,750 --> 01:39:22,041
Chinna...

1630
01:39:23,791 --> 01:39:25,000
A college student...

1631
01:39:25,125 --> 01:39:27,125
...was shot to death
by his own government!

1632
01:39:27,250 --> 01:39:29,041
This is a black day for our democracy!

1633
01:39:29,166 --> 01:39:30,916
Yes, it is!
-At ease!

1634
01:39:31,041 --> 01:39:32,125
At ease!

1635
01:39:32,250 --> 01:39:34,625
The deceased isn't a student!
He was a hooligan!

1636
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:37,500
Despite knowing Section 144 was in effect
in Chidambaram...

1637
01:39:37,625 --> 01:39:39,541
...he instigated students
to go on a procession!

1638
01:39:39,666 --> 01:39:41,875
He violently attacked police officers!

1639
01:39:42,000 --> 01:39:44,500
Do you expect us to put a medal on him?

1640
01:39:44,625 --> 01:39:49,000
I can firmly say you didn't
publicly declare Section 144 was in effect!

1641
01:39:49,125 --> 01:39:51,000
Those are tall tales,
honorable member!

1642
01:39:51,500 --> 01:39:54,916
The student was fully aware Section 144
was in effect, when he gathered the crowd!

1643
01:39:55,041 --> 01:39:56,041
That's the truth!

1644
01:39:56,166 --> 01:39:59,500
You can spin it any way you like,
as that student isn't alive to deny that!

1645
01:39:59,625 --> 01:40:02,375
Blaming them for your mistakes
is old politics!

1646
01:40:02,500 --> 01:40:04,250
Yes, indeed!
-Honorable Member!

1647
01:40:06,041 --> 01:40:09,041
There is nothing old or new
in politics!

1648
01:40:09,666 --> 01:40:12,250
After taking these recent incidents
into account...

1649
01:40:12,791 --> 01:40:16,375
To ensure the order of peace
is in effect in our state...

1650
01:40:16,500 --> 01:40:18,500
...and to protect our people...

1651
01:40:19,125 --> 01:40:25,625
...I announce the strict enforcement
of the DIR (Defence of India Rules) Law!

1652
01:40:25,750 --> 01:40:27,000
What?
-Mr. Chief Minister!

1653
01:40:27,125 --> 01:40:31,000
The British put the DIR law in place
to suppress freedom fighters!

1654
01:40:31,125 --> 01:40:33,541
But now, as soon as the authority
reached your grasp...

1655
01:40:33,666 --> 01:40:36,250
...you've become the very thing
you swore to destroy!

1656
01:40:36,375 --> 01:40:37,375
Speak up, everyone!

1657
01:40:37,500 --> 01:40:39,166
We severely condemn the DIR law!
-At ease!

1658
01:40:39,291 --> 01:40:40,625
Who will answer for this death?

1659
01:40:40,750 --> 01:40:44,166
(The Hindi song 'Waqt Ne Kiya Kya Haseen
Sitam' plays on the radio)

1660
01:41:31,250 --> 01:41:32,250
"Greetings."

1661
01:41:32,375 --> 01:41:35,125
"Regional News.
Professor's Radio."

1662
01:41:36,250 --> 01:41:37,666
"As teachers..."

1663
01:41:37,791 --> 01:41:39,875
...we are quitting
from the language protests.

1664
01:41:40,000 --> 01:41:44,250
"We regret having stood hand in hand
with students until now."

1665
01:41:44,375 --> 01:41:45,625
The student Chinnadurai...

1666
01:41:47,625 --> 01:41:49,125
Under the guise of a language war...

1667
01:41:49,500 --> 01:41:53,166
"...he assembled a group
to enforce and execute his own wishes."

1668
01:41:54,000 --> 01:41:55,041
"We condemn that."

1669
01:41:59,125 --> 01:42:00,125
Tamil Professor.

1670
01:42:03,375 --> 01:42:05,625
You forced me to talk like this,
you wretches!

1671
01:42:06,375 --> 01:42:08,875
When our people catch a glimpse
of biriyani...

1672
01:42:10,000 --> 01:42:11,416
...they'll let go of their dignity.

1673
01:42:15,875 --> 01:42:17,916
You've had to eat a lot of biriyani,
I see.

1674
01:42:20,791 --> 01:42:23,625
In the name of punishment posting,
I was relegated to a sewer!

1675
01:42:24,541 --> 01:42:25,541
For six years!

1676
01:42:26,250 --> 01:42:28,625
For six years,
I sought perilous missions...

1677
01:42:28,750 --> 01:42:31,250
...and earned my way back to the top
like a dog!

1678
01:42:32,041 --> 01:42:33,250
Did I eat biriyani?

1679
01:42:34,250 --> 01:42:35,541
Or did you let me eat it?

1680
01:42:38,125 --> 01:42:40,500
You? A criminal who burned down a train?
Seen as a hero!

1681
01:42:41,291 --> 01:42:43,000
I, who saved lives that day?

1682
01:42:44,000 --> 01:42:45,250
I got punished!

1683
01:42:46,791 --> 01:42:50,000
But now?
Both brothers are criminals!

1684
01:42:51,875 --> 01:42:53,375
You broke my trigger finger.

1685
01:42:54,125 --> 01:42:55,375
They said my career was over.

1686
01:42:56,041 --> 01:42:57,041
Did I give up?

1687
01:42:58,291 --> 01:43:00,750
Didn't I learn to do everything
with my left hand?

1688
01:43:03,416 --> 01:43:05,250
In the same way, we ask you
to learn Hindi.

1689
01:43:07,166 --> 01:43:11,750
But the two of you brothers
want to make students lazy...

1690
01:43:12,500 --> 01:43:14,750
...and intend to hamper
the nation's progress!

1691
01:43:15,500 --> 01:43:17,500
A gang that's against its own country!

1692
01:43:27,666 --> 01:43:28,791
The Sepoy Mut...

1693
01:43:34,000 --> 01:43:36,750
A hundred years
before the Sepoy Mutiny...

1694
01:43:37,500 --> 01:43:40,291
...it was Tamilians
who first opposed the British.

1695
01:43:42,625 --> 01:43:45,375
We don't need anyone to lecture us
about patriotism!

1696
01:43:49,250 --> 01:43:50,875
You're propagating national progress?

1697
01:43:52,000 --> 01:43:53,000
How is that?

1698
01:43:54,125 --> 01:43:56,166
After burying our fundamental rights?

1699
01:43:57,375 --> 01:43:58,416
On top of that grave?

1700
01:44:05,666 --> 01:44:08,000
Your brother lies exactly where he belongs.

1701
01:44:09,750 --> 01:44:12,166
We burned a corpse
that reeked of sewer stench!

1702
01:44:27,500 --> 01:44:29,250
I want all their names.

1703
01:44:30,666 --> 01:44:33,291
Give a statement
confessing you burned down that train.

1704
01:44:35,125 --> 01:44:36,666
You only killed one brother of mine.

1705
01:44:41,250 --> 01:44:43,125
There is an army.

1706
01:44:45,000 --> 01:44:47,041
There is a great army.

1707
01:44:48,875 --> 01:44:51,375
To protect my mother tongue...

1708
01:44:51,500 --> 01:44:53,625
...there is a great army!

1709
01:45:09,125 --> 01:45:10,875
I learned something from the KGB.

1710
01:45:12,791 --> 01:45:16,166
You can't get the truth out of anyone
by relentlessly torturing them.

1711
01:45:17,000 --> 01:45:19,750
Because beyond a point...

1712
01:45:21,250 --> 01:45:22,750
...the brain shuts down...

1713
01:45:22,875 --> 01:45:24,750
...and they'll have no idea what to do.

1714
01:45:25,750 --> 01:45:26,916
They'll lose their senses!

1715
01:45:37,416 --> 01:45:39,750
But I know you have no such limits.

1716
01:45:42,541 --> 01:45:45,000
No breaking point.

1717
01:45:45,875 --> 01:45:48,750
So, I can do this as long as I want!

1718
01:45:54,500 --> 01:45:56,500
Kill me.

1719
01:45:59,416 --> 01:46:02,375
You went through hell for six years
for letting me slip away once!

1720
01:46:03,375 --> 01:46:06,166
Let me slip away again,
your entire life will be a living hell!

1721
01:46:41,625 --> 01:46:42,625
Here.

1722
01:46:42,750 --> 01:46:45,250
Stab me with it
and escape.

1723
01:46:56,500 --> 01:46:57,500
Will you leave...

1724
01:46:58,125 --> 01:47:01,166
...or will you die at Thiru's hands
like your friend Govind did?

1725
01:47:14,916 --> 01:47:16,166
Who are you people?
Tell me!

1726
01:47:16,291 --> 01:47:17,500
(Hindi) Don't hit me!

1727
01:47:17,625 --> 01:47:20,041
Tell me the name of the man who hit me!
I'll let you go!

1728
01:47:20,500 --> 01:47:21,750
(Hindi) Please don't hit me!

1729
01:47:24,375 --> 01:47:25,625
(Hindi) Please don't kill me...

1730
01:47:30,541 --> 01:47:31,625
(Hindi) Listen, kid.

1731
01:47:33,000 --> 01:47:34,291
(Hindi) This isn't your fight.

1732
01:47:36,375 --> 01:47:37,500
(Hindi) The names.

1733
01:47:37,625 --> 01:47:38,875
(Hindi) Please don't kill me!

1734
01:47:39,000 --> 01:47:40,666
(Hindi) The names of your allies!

1735
01:47:42,666 --> 01:47:44,666
(Hindi) Just give me the names
of your allies!

1736
01:47:45,791 --> 01:47:46,791
(Hindi) Tell me!

1737
01:47:51,625 --> 01:47:53,291
(Hindi) Please don't kill me!

1738
01:47:59,875 --> 01:48:01,625
You were my only bloody clue!

1739
01:48:11,375 --> 01:48:13,750
Your friend didn't reveal your name
till the end.

1740
01:48:13,875 --> 01:48:15,916
Thiru won't follow protocol.
He'll just kill you.

1741
01:48:18,500 --> 01:48:19,625
Come on.

1742
01:48:19,750 --> 01:48:21,166
Go into hiding in Andhra Pradesh.

1743
01:48:22,166 --> 01:48:23,166
Trust me.

1744
01:48:23,875 --> 01:48:25,041
I'm a Tamilian too!

1745
01:48:29,375 --> 01:48:31,500
Will you tell us where Chezhiyan is or not?

1746
01:48:31,625 --> 01:48:33,500
Tell me where he is!
-Answer me!

1747
01:48:33,625 --> 01:48:35,000
Where have you hidden him?

1748
01:48:35,125 --> 01:48:36,625
Tell me!
Will you tell me or not?

1749
01:48:36,750 --> 01:48:39,125
If I arrest you all,
you'll be in jail for life!

1750
01:48:39,250 --> 01:48:42,125
Don't let anyone go
until they tell us where Chezhiyan is!

1751
01:48:42,250 --> 01:48:43,666
Get in the van!
-Answer me!

1752
01:48:43,791 --> 01:48:45,166
Where is Chezhiyan?

1753
01:48:45,291 --> 01:48:46,666
Tell the truth!

1754
01:48:46,791 --> 01:48:48,666
Where is he?
-The great Anna studied here!

1755
01:48:48,791 --> 01:48:50,291
Know what'll happen if he finds out?

1756
01:48:50,416 --> 01:48:52,250
Your precious Anna is also in jail!
Move!

1757
01:48:55,916 --> 01:48:56,916
Sir...

1758
01:48:57,750 --> 01:49:00,166
I tried my hardest to stop him.

1759
01:49:14,166 --> 01:49:15,541
Who the hell are you to strike me?

1760
01:49:16,000 --> 01:49:17,291
I'm an IB officer like you too!

1761
01:49:33,125 --> 01:49:34,416
Are you and I the same?

1762
01:49:35,416 --> 01:49:36,750
Traitor!

1763
01:49:39,416 --> 01:49:40,875
You hiding your grandson in here?

1764
01:49:41,000 --> 01:49:43,125
Where are you going?
Don't go in there!

1765
01:49:43,750 --> 01:49:44,916
Get up! Let's go!

1766
01:49:45,041 --> 01:49:46,375
Where's your leader?

1767
01:49:46,500 --> 01:49:48,541
Where is Chezhiyan?
-Tell me where he is!

1768
01:49:48,666 --> 01:49:49,791
Don't hit them!
-Get going!

1769
01:49:51,791 --> 01:49:52,875
Whack him!

1770
01:49:53,000 --> 01:49:54,875
I can't see!

1771
01:49:55,750 --> 01:49:56,750
Move!

1772
01:49:56,875 --> 01:49:58,875
Get in!
-We're just his neighbors!

1773
01:49:59,000 --> 01:50:00,500
Get in!
-Let us go!

1774
01:50:00,625 --> 01:50:01,666
Get in!

1775
01:50:10,125 --> 01:50:11,875
Hey! Get up!

1776
01:50:12,250 --> 01:50:13,291
Sir?

1777
01:50:20,000 --> 01:50:21,041
Thank you.

1778
01:50:21,166 --> 01:50:22,541
(Hindi) I don't need your thanks.

1779
01:50:23,416 --> 01:50:25,541
(Hindi) Your grandmother's cooking
will suffice.

1780
01:50:27,875 --> 01:50:29,125
(Hindi) Be safe, brother.

1781
01:50:38,791 --> 01:50:39,791
No one here, ma'am!

1782
01:50:39,916 --> 01:50:42,000
No one in this compartment, sir.
-Keep searching!

1783
01:50:42,125 --> 01:50:43,916
Check the next compartment, constable!

1784
01:50:44,041 --> 01:50:46,125
Check the engine, too!
-Yes, sir!

1785
01:50:47,125 --> 01:50:48,250
Go there!
-Okay, sir.

1786
01:51:29,000 --> 01:51:30,125
Chezhiya!
-Chezhiya!

1787
01:51:30,625 --> 01:51:32,125
(Hindi) What the hell happened?

1788
01:51:33,291 --> 01:51:34,291
The money order arrived.

1789
01:51:35,000 --> 01:51:36,000
What's the plan, Che?

1790
01:51:37,250 --> 01:51:39,875
Many Delhi University students are with us.

1791
01:51:40,375 --> 01:51:42,125
South Indians, North Indians...

1792
01:51:42,250 --> 01:51:44,000
Even Fine Arts students!

1793
01:51:44,500 --> 01:51:45,750
What's our plan?

1794
01:51:47,125 --> 01:51:48,125
It's dangerous.

1795
01:51:48,750 --> 01:51:50,750
Tell us something we don't know!

1796
01:51:51,250 --> 01:51:52,250
Let's go!

1797
01:51:53,625 --> 01:51:55,125
The target is the All Party Meeting.

1798
01:51:55,250 --> 01:51:57,791
Just set up the stuff.
I'll handle the rest myself.

1799
01:51:57,916 --> 01:51:59,625
You don't need this hassle!
-Nonsense!

1800
01:51:59,750 --> 01:52:01,250
This is a fight against oppression!

1801
01:52:01,375 --> 01:52:03,791
If we let it lie,
they'll keep escalating matters!

1802
01:52:03,916 --> 01:52:05,250
(Bengali) One by one...

1803
01:52:05,375 --> 01:52:07,250
They'll break our backbone!

1804
01:52:07,375 --> 01:52:09,916
But the Prime Minister
is at the China border, Chezhiya.

1805
01:52:10,041 --> 01:52:12,625
He won't be present
at tomorrow's All Party Meeting.

1806
01:52:12,750 --> 01:52:13,791
Let him stay there!

1807
01:52:13,916 --> 01:52:15,250
I'm here to meet someone else!

1808
01:52:15,375 --> 01:52:16,375
Whom?

1809
01:52:17,416 --> 01:52:19,500
You think it's so easy to meet her,
Chezhiya?

1810
01:52:39,125 --> 01:52:40,416
Tear it apart!

1811
01:52:50,291 --> 01:52:52,750
All the bus boards have been changed
overnight, ma'am!

1812
01:52:59,000 --> 01:53:01,125
What exactly have you written in Tamil?

1813
01:53:01,250 --> 01:53:02,375
They're fuming!

1814
01:53:02,500 --> 01:53:03,541
"Long Live Hindi."

1815
01:53:23,750 --> 01:53:24,750
I'm Chezhiyan!

1816
01:53:24,875 --> 01:53:26,000
From Madras, ma'am.

1817
01:53:28,625 --> 01:53:31,125
For just one day, we imposed a language
you don't understand.

1818
01:53:31,250 --> 01:53:32,250
Much like you did!

1819
01:53:33,000 --> 01:53:34,125
How does it taste?

1820
01:53:34,250 --> 01:53:35,291
Hey, Madrasi!

1821
01:53:35,416 --> 01:53:36,625
(Hindi) Get down from there!

1822
01:53:36,750 --> 01:53:38,375
These fellows don't know Hindi!

1823
01:53:39,041 --> 01:53:40,500
Brains are filled with sand!

1824
01:53:40,625 --> 01:53:42,500
Duffers, ma'am!
You should arrest them!

1825
01:53:45,375 --> 01:53:47,375
(Hindi) This was our only way
to meet you, ma'am.

1826
01:53:48,875 --> 01:53:51,500
(Hindi) I learned Hindi for six months.

1827
01:53:51,625 --> 01:53:52,916
(Hindi) But I stopped.

1828
01:53:53,375 --> 01:53:54,875
I stopped learning it, ma'am!

1829
01:53:55,416 --> 01:53:57,000
Not because I couldn't learn Hindi.

1830
01:53:57,625 --> 01:54:00,625
But because nobody has the right
to shove a language down my throat!

1831
01:54:02,916 --> 01:54:05,375
You first told us, "Just learn a few words
and that's enough".

1832
01:54:06,125 --> 01:54:09,416
Now you say we have to speak it as well
as those who've done so all their lives!

1833
01:54:10,500 --> 01:54:12,125
They're already at the finish line...

1834
01:54:12,250 --> 01:54:15,291
...while we start from the beginning
and we kill ourselves to run this race!

1835
01:54:15,750 --> 01:54:18,000
If we don't do that,
we are unemployable.

1836
01:54:18,541 --> 01:54:19,541
You won't hire us!

1837
01:54:19,666 --> 01:54:21,541
Are we not the citizens of this country,
ma'am?

1838
01:54:21,666 --> 01:54:22,666
We are!
-We are!

1839
01:54:22,791 --> 01:54:24,500
Ma'am!
He's a fugitive!

1840
01:54:25,125 --> 01:54:26,250
He has escaped from jail!

1841
01:54:27,041 --> 01:54:28,041
Really?

1842
01:54:29,125 --> 01:54:30,666
Got any record of that?

1843
01:54:31,375 --> 01:54:33,000
Do you have any records of my arrest?

1844
01:54:33,125 --> 01:54:34,125
An FIR copy?

1845
01:54:35,625 --> 01:54:37,500
All we wrote is "Long Live Hindi"!

1846
01:54:38,375 --> 01:54:39,750
And it must thrive in this city!

1847
01:54:40,916 --> 01:54:42,750
We only ask to let Tamil thrive
in our soil!

1848
01:54:47,416 --> 01:54:49,250
(Hindi) Your father gave us his word,
ma'am.

1849
01:54:50,166 --> 01:54:51,500
It's your father's vow.

1850
01:54:52,500 --> 01:54:53,875
You need to uphold it, ma'am.

1851
01:55:04,000 --> 01:55:06,291
We want justice!

1852
01:55:06,416 --> 01:55:08,125
We want justice!

1853
01:55:08,250 --> 01:55:10,666
We want justice!

1854
01:55:10,791 --> 01:55:12,875
We want justice!

1855
01:55:13,000 --> 01:55:14,625
We want justice!

1856
01:55:21,000 --> 01:55:23,625
But you don't seem to care about
the unity of this country.

1857
01:55:23,750 --> 01:55:25,250
In fact just the opposite, ma'am.

1858
01:55:26,500 --> 01:55:28,416
Unity in diversity
is the strength of our nation.

1859
01:55:29,791 --> 01:55:30,875
We want unity.

1860
01:55:31,000 --> 01:55:32,250
You want uniformity.

1861
01:55:32,375 --> 01:55:33,541
That's the difference.

1862
01:55:36,125 --> 01:55:37,125
Ma'am...

1863
01:55:37,250 --> 01:55:40,541
I ask for a referendum.
Let people vote for their future.

1864
01:55:42,625 --> 01:55:44,666
But referendums are not constitutional.

1865
01:55:44,791 --> 01:55:46,625
Then I ask for a signature campaign!

1866
01:55:46,750 --> 01:55:48,000
We'll seek endorsements.

1867
01:55:48,125 --> 01:55:49,875
Please hear the voice of the public.

1868
01:55:50,000 --> 01:55:52,125
As their representative,
take it to the Parliament.

1869
01:55:53,791 --> 01:55:55,000
Isn't that constitutional?

1870
01:55:58,166 --> 01:55:59,791
And you said he's an illiterate goon?

1871
01:55:59,916 --> 01:56:00,916
But ma'am...

1872
01:56:04,250 --> 01:56:05,750
So what is it you want?

1873
01:56:06,375 --> 01:56:07,500
Firstly, ma'am...

1874
01:56:07,625 --> 01:56:09,875
We want English to continue
as the official language.

1875
01:56:10,916 --> 01:56:12,250
But I can't decide that.

1876
01:56:13,250 --> 01:56:15,375
You don't have the support
in the Parliament.

1877
01:56:15,791 --> 01:56:19,375
And you definitely don't have
the 75% majority vote...

1878
01:56:19,500 --> 01:56:21,250
...from non-Hindi speaking states.

1879
01:56:22,041 --> 01:56:26,791
What if we prove that we have 75% support
from the students of all non-Hindi states?

1880
01:56:29,000 --> 01:56:30,750
They're the ones who will vote for you.

1881
01:56:33,625 --> 01:56:34,875
And how will you prove that?

1882
01:56:36,375 --> 01:56:38,666
The state government says
there's no dissent down south.

1883
01:56:39,750 --> 01:56:42,500
But I will prove that we're opposing
this imposition, ma'am.

1884
01:56:45,250 --> 01:56:48,375
But I'm assuming that the Tamil people
are not against Hindi.

1885
01:56:48,500 --> 01:56:50,375
Absolutely correct, ma'am!
100%!

1886
01:56:50,500 --> 01:56:52,625
We are not against Hindi
and we will never be.

1887
01:56:53,666 --> 01:56:56,291
We will oppose it only when you impose it
on us, ma'am.

1888
01:56:58,416 --> 01:56:59,416
Okay.

1889
01:57:00,500 --> 01:57:03,500
Show me the support when I come
to Coimbatore on February 12th.

1890
01:57:04,500 --> 01:57:05,791
You have seven days.

1891
01:57:05,916 --> 01:57:09,750
How do we show numbers when the state govt.
has imposed Section 144 on us?

1892
01:57:09,875 --> 01:57:10,875
Fair enough!

1893
01:57:11,625 --> 01:57:13,291
Section 144 will be revoked.

1894
01:57:13,416 --> 01:57:14,416
Ma'am...

1895
01:57:18,000 --> 01:57:19,625
But here's the thing, Mr. Chezhiyan.

1896
01:57:20,875 --> 01:57:23,500
While I understand your reasons
for today's protest...

1897
01:57:24,500 --> 01:57:26,125
...I do not appreciate
your methods.

1898
01:57:26,750 --> 01:57:27,750
It was wrong.

1899
01:57:28,916 --> 01:57:30,666
You should not have disturbed the public.

1900
01:57:33,666 --> 01:57:34,666
Sorry, ma'am.

1901
01:57:35,375 --> 01:57:38,041
We have decided to indulge
only in peaceful protests now on.

1902
01:57:39,041 --> 01:57:40,791
Please uphold our trust, ma'am.

1903
01:57:41,541 --> 01:57:42,625
We believe in you, ma'am.

1904
01:57:47,916 --> 01:57:51,625
So according to you, he's not going to be
able to demonstrate the right support, yes?

1905
01:57:51,750 --> 01:57:53,500
Not even one percent, ma'am!

1906
01:57:53,875 --> 01:57:55,750
Everyone's starving down there!

1907
01:57:55,875 --> 01:58:00,750
Will those people tend to their hunger,
or focus on this silly protest?

1908
01:58:01,291 --> 01:58:03,625
Then why must you worry? You shouldn't.
-Yes, ma'am.

1909
01:58:04,750 --> 01:58:05,875
You must understand.

1910
01:58:06,541 --> 01:58:10,041
The only way to end this,
is to allow him to do this.

1911
01:58:11,250 --> 01:58:14,250
To lose in the eyes of the public
once and for all.

1912
01:58:15,625 --> 01:58:16,625
And if he wins?

1913
01:58:17,541 --> 01:58:21,291
We're not bound to accept that decision.
-Yes.

1914
01:58:24,041 --> 01:58:26,416
"A Tamil protest
that brought Delhi to a standstill!"

1915
01:58:27,291 --> 01:58:31,000
So far, the voice of protestors
would only echo through Madras State!

1916
01:58:31,750 --> 01:58:34,250
It has even reached Delhi now!
-Indeed, sir!

1917
01:58:34,375 --> 01:58:36,375
Are you behind this, Mr. Anna?

1918
01:58:36,791 --> 01:58:38,166
No, sir.
We are not behind this.

1919
01:58:39,250 --> 01:58:41,625
But whoever did this
is a brother of mine!

1920
01:58:42,250 --> 01:58:44,125
But whoever has done this
is my brother!

1921
01:58:44,250 --> 01:58:47,625
'She, who is like a flowering vine
that smiles like the moon'

1922
01:58:47,750 --> 01:58:50,625
'She, who is like a flowering vine
that smiles like the moon'

1923
01:58:53,875 --> 01:58:56,875
'With her honey lips,
she will endow the essence of life'

1924
01:58:57,000 --> 01:58:59,375
'As you savor it drop by drop,
she will bend her head shyly'

1925
01:59:01,666 --> 01:59:05,125
They think we're just young punks
who can't achieve anything!

1926
01:59:06,250 --> 01:59:07,291
Let them!

1927
01:59:09,666 --> 01:59:11,000
An army is needed!

1928
01:59:11,125 --> 01:59:12,500
An army is needed!

1929
01:59:12,625 --> 01:59:14,291
A great army is needed!

1930
01:59:14,416 --> 01:59:15,875
A great army is needed!

1931
01:59:16,000 --> 01:59:18,875
A great army is needed
to safeguard Tamil!

1932
01:59:19,000 --> 01:59:21,500
'O army of comrades'

1933
01:59:21,750 --> 01:59:24,000
'Let's go to war'

1934
01:59:24,125 --> 01:59:26,416
'Be it life or death...'
-Ensure no one finds out.

1935
01:59:26,541 --> 01:59:28,750
'...we shall face it together'

1936
01:59:28,875 --> 01:59:33,625
'With courage,
we will seek answers'

1937
01:59:33,750 --> 01:59:37,750
'As a roaring wildfire,
we will reclaim justice'

1938
01:59:38,541 --> 01:59:43,166
'Without seeing the light of change,
these eyes shall sleep not'

1939
01:59:43,291 --> 01:59:47,125
'Even if bullets pierce our chests,
our quest for truth will cease not'

1940
01:59:47,250 --> 01:59:50,500
What crap! What good will come of them?
Look at the trash he's reading!

1941
01:59:50,625 --> 01:59:52,875
'We will guard our motherland
now and forever'

1942
01:59:53,000 --> 01:59:55,166
'We took to arms that day'

1943
01:59:55,291 --> 01:59:57,625
'Even a calf will pounce in an attack'

1944
01:59:57,750 --> 02:00:00,125
'A needless, needless law...'
-Steer clear of the cops!

1945
02:00:00,250 --> 02:00:02,416
'Won't the arrogance
of those in power fall?'

1946
02:00:02,541 --> 02:00:04,625
'Our blood boils to stir us on'

1947
02:00:04,750 --> 02:00:06,875
'A war of blazing passion'

1948
02:00:08,625 --> 02:00:09,625
(Telugu) Dear...

1949
02:00:14,875 --> 02:00:16,625
Will you kill this old crone, dear?

1950
02:00:16,750 --> 02:00:19,041
Without Chinna or Chezhiya,
I don't care who lives or dies!

1951
02:00:19,500 --> 02:00:20,500
(Telugu) Dear...

1952
02:00:20,875 --> 02:00:22,125
That soda guy is here.

1953
02:00:23,125 --> 02:00:24,541
Go.
-A money order from Chezhiyan.

1954
02:00:24,666 --> 02:00:26,875
'Vanquishing oppressors
does not count as sins'

1955
02:00:27,000 --> 02:00:28,250
'Set off like a storm'

1956
02:00:29,291 --> 02:00:30,541
'Set off like a storm'

1957
02:00:31,875 --> 02:00:34,291
'When your wings are torn apart,
stand not with patience'

1958
02:00:34,416 --> 02:00:36,750
'If you rise with fury,
the oppression cannot go on'

1959
02:00:36,875 --> 02:00:38,250
'Be the action'

1960
02:00:39,125 --> 02:00:40,625
'Be the action'

1961
02:00:41,625 --> 02:00:43,875
'If there's evil afoot...'

1962
02:00:44,000 --> 02:00:46,166
'...mustn't it be quelled?'

1963
02:00:46,291 --> 02:00:48,416
'Cowards, we shall never be'

1964
02:00:48,541 --> 02:00:49,875
Chinna was right.

1965
02:00:50,000 --> 02:00:52,541
Comrades of both Gandhiji and Netaji
laid down their lives.

1966
02:00:52,666 --> 02:00:55,875
Another war of independence!
-'A day has a dawn and a dusk'

1967
02:00:56,000 --> 02:00:58,166
'Waging war is the way to victory'

1968
02:00:58,291 --> 02:01:00,666
'Let's get this done,
one way or the other'

1969
02:01:01,125 --> 02:01:03,250
"Mere spectators, this puppet government!"

1970
02:01:04,000 --> 02:01:05,375
"A spineless government."

1971
02:01:05,916 --> 02:01:09,500
"A disgraceful, shameless,
unjust government."

1972
02:01:09,625 --> 02:01:13,625
The opposition is ripping you apart
at the assembly with these words!

1973
02:01:24,750 --> 02:01:27,041
'Our war is for the liberation of Tamil'

1974
02:01:27,166 --> 02:01:29,375
'Shatter the obstacles
and leave our foes to dust'

1975
02:01:29,500 --> 02:01:30,791
'As mountains,
we shall rise'

1976
02:01:31,666 --> 02:01:33,250
'Reclaim our birthright,
we shall'

1977
02:01:34,416 --> 02:01:36,625
'Let the feeling
that Tamil is our life soar'

1978
02:01:36,750 --> 02:01:38,875
'Even if the end approaches...'

1979
02:01:39,000 --> 02:01:41,125
'...let's fight injustice'

1980
02:01:41,250 --> 02:01:43,875
'As a fire, let's blaze...
We shall never hesitate to rage'

1981
02:01:44,000 --> 02:01:48,750
'The culture that taught justice
to the custodians of justice...'

1982
02:01:48,875 --> 02:01:52,250
'How can we accept the orders
of the oppressors?'

1983
02:01:53,500 --> 02:01:58,250
'The culture known for its compassion
even to a jasmine vine...'

1984
02:01:58,375 --> 02:02:01,250
'How can we accept trouble
and be ruined?'

1985
02:02:01,375 --> 02:02:03,125
'Let's get this done,
one way or the other'

1986
02:02:03,250 --> 02:02:05,416
'O army of comrades'

1987
02:02:05,541 --> 02:02:07,416
'Let's go to war'

1988
02:02:08,000 --> 02:02:10,250
'Be it life or death...'

1989
02:02:10,375 --> 02:02:12,125
'...we shall face it together'

1990
02:02:12,750 --> 02:02:16,791
'With courage,
we will seek answers'

1991
02:02:17,625 --> 02:02:21,791
'As a roaring wildfire,
we will reclaim justice'

1992
02:02:25,166 --> 02:02:26,166
May I sit, sir?

1993
02:02:26,916 --> 02:02:27,916
Sit the hell down!

1994
02:02:28,500 --> 02:02:29,666
As if you have manners!

1995
02:02:30,125 --> 02:02:32,875
I had flagged all post offices
in Delhi.

1996
02:02:33,000 --> 02:02:34,250
After the protest...

1997
02:02:34,375 --> 02:02:36,791
...22 money orders were sent,
all for the same amount!

1998
02:02:38,291 --> 02:02:39,291
So?

1999
02:02:39,416 --> 02:02:40,416
12.02 rupees.

2000
02:02:41,125 --> 02:02:43,625
Twelfth day, second month.
February 12.

2001
02:02:45,500 --> 02:02:46,625
What?

2002
02:02:46,750 --> 02:02:49,875
All along, they've used a sum to represent
the day of their operation.

2003
02:02:50,000 --> 02:02:51,291
The day of their operation.

2004
02:02:51,750 --> 02:02:53,000
Turn it around and take a look.

2005
02:02:56,791 --> 02:03:00,250
"We'll meet in Pollachi.
Through Aaliyar forest from Valparai."

2006
02:03:01,625 --> 02:03:02,625
"Gandhi."

2007
02:03:05,125 --> 02:03:06,375
What language script is this?

2008
02:03:06,500 --> 02:03:08,750
Brahmi. 2,000 years old.

2009
02:03:10,250 --> 02:03:11,250
How do you know?

2010
02:03:11,375 --> 02:03:14,375
In the last six years, I learned
every iteration of the Tamil script.

2011
02:03:15,916 --> 02:03:18,166
I let these money orders go through.

2012
02:03:19,125 --> 02:03:20,916
Shall I say why, Mr. Chief Minister?

2013
02:03:21,416 --> 02:03:22,541
It says 'Gandhi'.

2014
02:03:22,666 --> 02:03:24,875
It definitely must be the Gandhi Memorial
in Madurai.

2015
02:03:25,000 --> 02:03:27,625
You know what happened there
and who showed up.

2016
02:03:28,166 --> 02:03:32,166
The entire Puranaanooru gang who burned
down a train are coming to Pollachi.

2017
02:03:34,250 --> 02:03:37,125
Just one of them
brought Delhi to its knees!

2018
02:03:37,750 --> 02:03:39,000
Don't worry, sir.

2019
02:03:39,125 --> 02:03:40,916
Not a single signature will reach Delhi.

2020
02:03:41,041 --> 02:03:43,375
Because not a single one of them
will reach Coimbatore.

2021
02:03:44,375 --> 02:03:45,375
I need your orders.

2022
02:03:46,375 --> 02:03:47,375
But...

2023
02:03:48,416 --> 02:03:51,000
Isn't the state police
entirely at your command?

2024
02:03:52,125 --> 02:03:53,625
I don't need state police.

2025
02:03:53,750 --> 02:03:54,750
Why?

2026
02:03:54,875 --> 02:03:56,125
Look at their names!

2027
02:03:56,250 --> 02:03:58,916
Tamilkumaran, Tamilarasan, Tamilvendan...
Tamil everywhere!

2028
02:03:59,041 --> 02:04:00,375
I can't do shit with them!

2029
02:04:02,000 --> 02:04:03,750
I want a special task force.

2030
02:04:06,250 --> 02:04:07,291
My requisition.

2031
02:04:07,416 --> 02:04:11,750
Non-Tamil speaking police and personnel
from other states.

2032
02:04:11,875 --> 02:04:12,875
Immediately.

2033
02:04:13,500 --> 02:04:14,541
There won't be any media.

2034
02:04:16,125 --> 02:04:18,541
We'll wipe them out
and bury them in Pollachi.

2035
02:04:19,250 --> 02:04:20,416
The public will never know.

2036
02:04:21,125 --> 02:04:22,875
Come! Park here!

2037
02:04:23,500 --> 02:04:25,500
No problems on the way, Vaigarai?
-No.

2038
02:04:25,625 --> 02:04:27,625
Haven't seen you all in six years!
-Brother!

2039
02:04:27,750 --> 02:04:30,791
I've had our boys stashed away
all across Pollachi!

2040
02:04:30,916 --> 02:04:32,541
Don't worry.
We'll take care of them.

2041
02:04:32,666 --> 02:04:34,125
Signatures arrive safely?

2042
02:04:35,416 --> 02:04:37,250
Where are the kids from the other states?

2043
02:04:37,375 --> 02:04:38,750
Michael, Chacko and the rest?

2044
02:04:39,750 --> 02:04:40,875
Just our state, huh?

2045
02:04:42,125 --> 02:04:44,000
We need them to get the majority, right?

2046
02:04:44,125 --> 02:04:46,666
We'll have to make do
with those who are here by dawn.

2047
02:04:48,375 --> 02:04:50,750
Been years since you all tasted this soda!
Open one up!

2048
02:04:51,916 --> 02:04:53,875
Park these vans in the grove, Palanisamy!

2049
02:04:54,000 --> 02:04:55,000
Let's go! Come on!

2050
02:04:55,125 --> 02:04:56,625
Not a single van should be seen here!

2051
02:04:56,750 --> 02:04:58,000
Come along, Poovai!

2052
02:04:58,125 --> 02:04:59,541
I'll go to my Grandma's tonight.

2053
02:04:59,666 --> 02:05:01,416
I'll bring the guys over before dawn!

2054
02:05:02,000 --> 02:05:03,250
Be safe.
-Will do!

2055
02:05:08,250 --> 02:05:09,250
Hold this!

2056
02:05:16,000 --> 02:05:17,125
Sir!

2057
02:05:17,250 --> 02:05:19,791
No chance a single student
has crossed this check post.

2058
02:05:28,375 --> 02:05:29,375
It's time, Chezhiya.

2059
02:05:30,000 --> 02:05:31,916
I don't think those guys are coming.

2060
02:05:32,666 --> 02:05:33,666
Chezhiya!

2061
02:05:35,000 --> 02:05:36,041
I have an idea!

2062
02:05:36,166 --> 02:05:38,791
There's something called pirate radio.
We can talk on that!

2063
02:05:38,916 --> 02:05:41,000
We can tell the world
what's happening here.

2064
02:05:41,125 --> 02:05:42,416
At Dhanushkodi last year...

2065
02:05:42,541 --> 02:05:45,125
Enough! Stick to just screwing around
electric wires!

2066
02:05:45,250 --> 02:05:48,041
Like you're Sarojini Naidu
who can sing like a bird on the mic!

2067
02:05:48,166 --> 02:05:50,625
And she claims she can save Tamil!

2068
02:05:50,750 --> 02:05:54,375
She fancies she can save it all
with radio parts she stole!

2069
02:05:55,000 --> 02:05:56,041
Listen!

2070
02:05:56,166 --> 02:05:57,625
I was born and raised here!

2071
02:05:58,250 --> 02:06:00,250
I'm just as much Tamil as you are!

2072
02:06:01,041 --> 02:06:02,166
Understand this!

2073
02:06:02,791 --> 02:06:06,791
If Telugu is named the national language,
I will be the first to protest against it!

2074
02:06:14,375 --> 02:06:15,750
"How can I talk in the radio?"

2075
02:06:15,875 --> 02:06:18,166
"You already know the answer, Ratna."

2076
02:06:18,291 --> 02:06:21,500
"This government has every radio station
and newspaper in its pocket!"

2077
02:06:21,625 --> 02:06:24,750
"They decide what news
the public gets to hear and read!"

2078
02:06:25,375 --> 02:06:26,416
"We need to shatter that."

2079
02:06:27,375 --> 02:06:29,416
"Are radio waves their birthright?"

2080
02:06:30,000 --> 02:06:32,125
"They can hear it even if we talk, right?"

2081
02:06:32,250 --> 02:06:33,625
"Speak, Ratna!"

2082
02:06:34,416 --> 02:06:35,750
"We'll see what they do!"

2083
02:06:40,000 --> 02:06:43,625
From a certain height
and a certain angle...

2084
02:06:43,750 --> 02:06:45,541
...we can broadcast
across long distances.

2085
02:06:46,791 --> 02:06:50,291
We can even hack into the frequency
of National Radio!

2086
02:06:52,000 --> 02:06:53,125
Signal intrusion.

2087
02:06:54,625 --> 02:06:56,250
I learned it from the enemy, Mister.

2088
02:06:57,500 --> 02:06:58,500
Highly risky.

2089
02:06:59,375 --> 02:07:00,500
But it's doable!

2090
02:07:01,125 --> 02:07:03,750
We should use it to tell the world
what's happening here!

2091
02:07:07,291 --> 02:07:09,375
(Telugu) Who the hell are you
to question me?

2092
02:07:09,500 --> 02:07:12,000
(Telugu) You can't speak two languages
even to save your life!

2093
02:07:12,125 --> 02:07:14,166
(Telugu) I'll rip your tongue out, jackass!

2094
02:07:14,291 --> 02:07:16,125
(Telugu) Brainless oaf!

2095
02:07:16,916 --> 02:07:19,125
(Telugu) Who the hell are you
to question me?

2096
02:07:20,875 --> 02:07:23,916
Hey... She's saying something in Telugu.

2097
02:07:24,500 --> 02:07:25,500
I don't follow!

2098
02:07:26,625 --> 02:07:28,500
She can cuss in all languages!

2099
02:07:39,541 --> 02:07:40,541
Michael Reddy!

2100
02:07:47,625 --> 02:07:48,625
Shariffa!

2101
02:07:49,541 --> 02:07:50,541
Welcome!

2102
02:07:51,250 --> 02:07:52,250
Chezhiya!

2103
02:07:52,375 --> 02:07:53,916
Welcome!

2104
02:07:54,041 --> 02:07:55,750
Chezhiya!
-How are you, Singh?

2105
02:07:55,875 --> 02:07:56,875
I'm good. How about you?

2106
02:07:58,375 --> 02:07:59,875
When I saw the codeword 'Gandhi'...

2107
02:08:00,750 --> 02:08:02,916
...I knew I had to come here
even if it costs me my life!

2108
02:08:03,041 --> 02:08:05,416
The first money order in six years!
How could I not come?

2109
02:08:05,541 --> 02:08:07,541
How'd you get past the cops?

2110
02:08:07,666 --> 02:08:10,250
We parked at Udumalaipettai
and took the freight train!

2111
02:08:10,375 --> 02:08:12,666
That's how we get the goods
for our mill!

2112
02:08:13,291 --> 02:08:15,750
Chacko couldn't make it, Che.

2113
02:08:16,625 --> 02:08:19,250
He was summoned
for a government operation.

2114
02:08:19,375 --> 02:08:21,000
Only Kerala signatures aren't here yet?

2115
02:08:21,125 --> 02:08:22,750
Come, let's go eat!
-Brother!

2116
02:08:23,916 --> 02:08:25,041
It's okay. We'll handle it.

2117
02:08:25,500 --> 02:08:28,250
You guys have come from all over
the nation to save a mother tongue!

2118
02:08:28,375 --> 02:08:30,375
What kind of man would I be
if I didn't feed our kin?

2119
02:08:31,250 --> 02:08:33,750
Come along, everyone!

2120
02:08:35,791 --> 02:08:37,291
Eat as much as you want!

2121
02:08:38,250 --> 02:08:40,041
(Telugu) Eat well!

2122
02:08:40,750 --> 02:08:43,000
Serve some to the Bengali girl!
-(Kannada) Chow down!

2123
02:08:43,666 --> 02:08:47,125
(Bengali) Eating on banana leaves
seems to be a staple of Tamil culture.

2124
02:08:47,250 --> 02:08:48,625
(Bengali) Great food, right?

2125
02:08:49,416 --> 02:08:50,750
(Telugu) Damn! So spicy!

2126
02:08:51,625 --> 02:08:53,916
Come to Madurai
and we'll gorge down spiny loach soup!

2127
02:08:55,041 --> 02:08:56,500
No food like Madurai food!

2128
02:08:57,166 --> 02:09:00,041
(Kannada) Come over to my place!
You won't see food like ours anywhere!

2129
02:09:03,250 --> 02:09:04,541
This is our India right here!

2130
02:09:04,666 --> 02:09:07,916
Banana leaves loaded with stew,
vegetables, lentil curry, tamarind stew...

2131
02:09:08,041 --> 02:09:09,375
Like a feast!

2132
02:09:09,500 --> 02:09:11,375
But what does this damn government say?

2133
02:09:11,500 --> 02:09:13,875
They're trying to turn India
into a land without diversity!

2134
02:09:14,000 --> 02:09:15,000
The dumbos!

2135
02:09:15,125 --> 02:09:17,125
(Telugu) Hit the nail in the head!
-Spot on!

2136
02:09:18,750 --> 02:09:19,750
Eat well!

2137
02:09:21,500 --> 02:09:23,750
Relax. We'll mop the floor with them!

2138
02:09:23,875 --> 02:09:25,250
(Kannada) Well said!

2139
02:09:30,500 --> 02:09:31,625
Leave in half an hour.

2140
02:09:42,166 --> 02:09:44,375
Attention, citizens!

2141
02:09:45,250 --> 02:09:48,125
Turn in the students who are hiding
in your town immediately!

2142
02:09:49,000 --> 02:09:50,875
I have shooting orders!

2143
02:09:52,541 --> 02:09:54,666
Why must you die for those miscreants?

2144
02:09:55,916 --> 02:09:57,791
How did this mongrel pick up our scent?

2145
02:09:59,750 --> 02:10:00,875
He read my tattoo.

2146
02:10:03,000 --> 02:10:04,375
He saw the money orders.

2147
02:10:05,625 --> 02:10:06,625
He understands Brahmi!

2148
02:10:07,500 --> 02:10:08,666
How did this slip past me?

2149
02:10:09,625 --> 02:10:10,625
But...

2150
02:10:11,125 --> 02:10:13,916
But why did he let money orders through
and get us here?

2151
02:10:18,541 --> 02:10:19,750
Brother Thambi?

2152
02:10:19,875 --> 02:10:22,000
Is there another way in to Coimbatore?

2153
02:10:23,500 --> 02:10:24,500
No, there isn't.

2154
02:10:25,000 --> 02:10:27,500
There is a way. But...

2155
02:10:33,791 --> 02:10:34,791
Sir!

2156
02:10:35,625 --> 02:10:36,625
Forces are here, sir.

2157
02:10:36,750 --> 02:10:38,916
(Malayalam) It's all quiet.
There's no issue here!

2158
02:10:39,041 --> 02:10:40,125
Hey!

2159
02:10:40,250 --> 02:10:42,000
We already told you there's nobody here!

2160
02:10:42,125 --> 02:10:43,125
Leave!

2161
02:10:45,625 --> 02:10:46,625
Get going!

2162
02:10:47,625 --> 02:10:49,291
Please leave!

2163
02:10:51,125 --> 02:10:52,750
(Malayalam) There seems to be no issue.

2164
02:10:52,875 --> 02:10:54,166
Then create one!

2165
02:10:59,625 --> 02:11:02,000
This is how the factory's sewage
reaches the Aliyar river.

2166
02:11:02,125 --> 02:11:04,375
You can use it to get to the outskirts
of town!

2167
02:11:04,500 --> 02:11:06,000
Easy to reach the main road from there!

2168
02:11:07,625 --> 02:11:09,291
Sir...
-(Malayalam) Search that side!

2169
02:11:09,416 --> 02:11:10,625
What's going on, sir?

2170
02:11:11,166 --> 02:11:12,875
(Malayalam) We got one!
-Let go of me.

2171
02:11:13,000 --> 02:11:14,375
(Malayalam) Come!
-Let go of him!

2172
02:11:14,500 --> 02:11:15,500
Let go!

2173
02:11:15,625 --> 02:11:18,625
Please spare my grandson!
-(Malayalam) Don't let him escape!

2174
02:11:18,750 --> 02:11:19,875
Let go!

2175
02:11:20,000 --> 02:11:21,541
Why are you arresting me?

2176
02:11:21,666 --> 02:11:23,000
Let go of my hand!

2177
02:11:23,125 --> 02:11:24,625
Let go!
-(Malayalam) I'll whack you!

2178
02:11:28,166 --> 02:11:29,791
Please let him go, sir.
He's innocent!

2179
02:11:39,375 --> 02:11:41,291
This is the reason for the trouble, right?
Watch!

2180
02:11:43,875 --> 02:11:45,625
Careful!
-Come quickly!

2181
02:11:45,750 --> 02:11:47,750
One at a time!
-Hurry!

2182
02:11:47,875 --> 02:11:49,000
Watch your step, dear!

2183
02:11:49,125 --> 02:11:50,500
(Hindi) Careful, Ratna!
-Be safe!

2184
02:11:50,916 --> 02:11:52,666
He smeared dung on the post office board.

2185
02:11:53,541 --> 02:11:55,291
Is it still quiet, Commander?

2186
02:11:59,291 --> 02:12:02,416
They killed him! Is there no one
to question this injustice?

2187
02:12:04,375 --> 02:12:05,750
My dear boy!

2188
02:12:11,416 --> 02:12:13,500
Forces!
Lathi charge!

2189
02:12:13,625 --> 02:12:16,000
Come on!
Charge!

2190
02:12:32,125 --> 02:12:33,416
I'm not leaving you behind.

2191
02:12:34,750 --> 02:12:37,416
If our last stand is deemed to be
in Pollachi, so be it!

2192
02:12:38,500 --> 02:12:40,500
What's the point if we all perish here?

2193
02:12:41,125 --> 02:12:43,375
Our army and these signatures
need to reach Coimbatore!

2194
02:12:43,500 --> 02:12:45,666
Gather everyone and leave!
I'll come with the van!

2195
02:12:57,250 --> 02:12:58,250
Leave them alone!

2196
02:12:58,375 --> 02:12:59,875
You killed my grandson!

2197
02:13:03,500 --> 02:13:04,750
The mob is attacking us, sir!

2198
02:13:04,875 --> 02:13:06,750
We're suffering casualties!
We need backup!

2199
02:13:07,666 --> 02:13:08,666
You may leave.

2200
02:13:25,500 --> 02:13:27,625
I'll have the vans drop off the goods.

2201
02:13:28,625 --> 02:13:29,750
Travel safe!

2202
02:13:31,125 --> 02:13:32,500
Victory and courage to us all!

2203
02:15:00,375 --> 02:15:01,625
Won't answer me, huh?

2204
02:15:02,750 --> 02:15:04,625
Just turn in the students
and the signatures.

2205
02:15:09,291 --> 02:15:11,000
Rifle Company!
Open fire!

2206
02:15:15,625 --> 02:15:21,166
These mongrels have decided
to turn Pollachi into a cemetery?

2207
02:15:26,875 --> 02:15:28,375
Hey! Come on!

2208
02:15:28,500 --> 02:15:29,541
Come along, Ratna!

2209
02:15:29,666 --> 02:15:31,875
I have an important errand to run.
Be right back.

2210
02:15:32,000 --> 02:15:33,791
Go on.
-Are you insane?

2211
02:15:33,916 --> 02:15:35,875
They're shooting us down
without any restraint!

2212
02:15:36,000 --> 02:15:37,000
Come along, I say!

2213
02:15:42,000 --> 02:15:43,000
Go on.

2214
02:15:43,500 --> 02:15:44,500
Be safe.

2215
02:15:46,125 --> 02:15:47,916
Let's go!
Come on!

2216
02:15:58,291 --> 02:15:59,625
I have a child, sir!

2217
02:16:00,250 --> 02:16:02,375
Please tell them not to fire, sir!

2218
02:16:21,791 --> 02:16:23,125
We caught the students, sir.

2219
02:16:42,750 --> 02:16:45,000
Answer my question
only with the truth.

2220
02:16:46,166 --> 02:16:47,416
Where is Chezhiyan?

2221
02:16:48,375 --> 02:16:49,375
Sir!

2222
02:16:50,500 --> 02:16:52,750
Found the signed papers?
-No, sir.

2223
02:16:59,875 --> 02:17:01,500
One by one, all of you will die!

2224
02:17:02,125 --> 02:17:04,250
Tell me!
Where is Chezhiyan?

2225
02:17:05,125 --> 02:17:06,125
I don't know, sir.

2226
02:17:09,375 --> 02:17:12,125
If you couldn't find the papers,
it doesn't mean they're not here!

2227
02:17:12,875 --> 02:17:14,125
Go search!
-Yes, sir!

2228
02:17:17,000 --> 02:17:18,750
Every single one of you are suspects!

2229
02:17:19,375 --> 02:17:21,750
You! You! You!
All of you are suspects!

2230
02:17:21,875 --> 02:17:24,125
If I toss you in jail,
you'll be there for life!

2231
02:17:24,250 --> 02:17:26,125
Please, sir... No...
-Where is Chezhiyan?

2232
02:17:26,250 --> 02:17:27,416
Where the hell is he?

2233
02:17:27,541 --> 02:17:29,166
I swear I don't know!

2234
02:17:31,125 --> 02:17:32,125
Sir!

2235
02:17:32,250 --> 02:17:33,625
Why are you doing this to us?

2236
02:18:21,250 --> 02:18:22,250
You found your target.

2237
02:18:23,625 --> 02:18:24,625
Let these people go.

2238
02:18:26,041 --> 02:18:27,041
Sir!

2239
02:18:27,166 --> 02:18:28,500
All the signatures are in there!

2240
02:18:30,541 --> 02:18:31,666
Burn them.

2241
02:18:31,791 --> 02:18:32,875
Burn them all.

2242
02:19:00,625 --> 02:19:02,000
Where the hell are the papers?

2243
02:19:02,125 --> 02:19:03,375
Tricking me with empty sheets?

2244
02:19:15,000 --> 02:19:17,125
You took your own sweet time, Major!
You're late!

2245
02:19:18,000 --> 02:19:20,416
Shoot all of them
and burn them all!

2246
02:19:21,041 --> 02:19:23,125
There must be no evidence
of this entire incident!

2247
02:19:23,250 --> 02:19:24,875
History should have no record of this!

2248
02:19:27,375 --> 02:19:28,541
Major!

2249
02:19:29,125 --> 02:19:30,500
Don't shoot him!
I need him!

2250
02:19:36,625 --> 02:19:37,625
Brother Thambi!

2251
02:19:38,291 --> 02:19:39,875
Do you know to drive this thing
or not?

2252
02:19:40,375 --> 02:19:41,666
My first time, buddy!

2253
02:19:41,791 --> 02:19:43,166
The drivers usually handle this!

2254
02:19:44,125 --> 02:19:45,250
Don't be scared!

2255
02:19:45,375 --> 02:19:47,250
Just watch how we reach our destination!

2256
02:19:47,375 --> 02:19:48,500
Where?
-Where, brother?

2257
02:19:49,250 --> 02:19:51,000
Where are we going?
-"Where are we going"?

2258
02:19:51,375 --> 02:19:53,291
Where else? Coimbatore!
-Seems unlikely!

2259
02:20:09,666 --> 02:20:10,666
Police!

2260
02:20:11,375 --> 02:20:14,666
Come what may, that lady doesn't leave
without seeing the signatures!

2261
02:20:14,791 --> 02:20:16,000
I'll handle the cops.

2262
02:20:16,125 --> 02:20:17,500
(Telugu) Be careful, Shariffa.

2263
02:20:17,625 --> 02:20:19,250
(Telugu) Take care.
-(Kannada) I will.

2264
02:20:22,000 --> 02:20:23,250
Careful, Michael!

2265
02:20:25,250 --> 02:20:26,750
(Kannada) Be alert,
Michael Reddy!

2266
02:20:31,541 --> 02:20:33,500
(Malayalam) One of them is getting away!
Get him!

2267
02:20:55,125 --> 02:20:57,750
(Kannada) Don't stop, brother!
Keep going!

2268
02:21:06,500 --> 02:21:07,500
Michael!

2269
02:21:41,875 --> 02:21:42,875
Come in, Gauri!

2270
02:21:45,500 --> 02:21:46,875
The minister's life is in danger!

2271
02:21:47,500 --> 02:21:49,916
Get her out of the Coimbatore station
immediately!

2272
02:21:50,625 --> 02:21:51,625
I can't hear you, sir.

2273
02:21:51,750 --> 02:21:52,750
Come in, Gauri!

2274
02:21:53,875 --> 02:21:56,500
The minister's life is in jeopardy!
Get her out of the station!

2275
02:22:03,166 --> 02:22:04,750
Hoist it that side!
Can't get a signal!

2276
02:22:14,250 --> 02:22:15,375
Got it!
-Got it?

2277
02:22:15,500 --> 02:22:16,500
Yes!

2278
02:22:21,875 --> 02:22:23,750
For a human to think...

2279
02:22:24,375 --> 02:22:25,666
...the most impor...

2280
02:22:25,791 --> 02:22:28,916
...important tool...

2281
02:22:29,750 --> 02:22:31,791
...is... is...

2282
02:22:31,916 --> 02:22:32,916
...language!

2283
02:22:50,750 --> 02:22:53,250
Destroying a language
is akin to destroying one's identity.

2284
02:22:53,750 --> 02:22:56,666
An individual without an identity
can easily be enslaved.

2285
02:22:57,750 --> 02:22:59,250
Language politics in a nutshell!

2286
02:23:00,916 --> 02:23:04,541
Destroying my mother tongue is akin
to destroying my ability to think.

2287
02:23:06,125 --> 02:23:09,041
If we are unable to think,
how can we ever make progress?

2288
02:23:11,250 --> 02:23:12,750
That's what they want.

2289
02:23:14,750 --> 02:23:18,875
To show your support for Tamil,
assemble at the Coimbatore Junction!

2290
02:23:27,000 --> 02:23:29,000
Go for field radio officer, 13th Company,
over!

2291
02:23:29,750 --> 02:23:31,166
Special Officer Thiru here!
Over!

2292
02:23:31,291 --> 02:23:33,041
Reading loud and clear!
I await your order!

2293
02:23:33,166 --> 02:23:36,666
They've planted bombs on a freight train
heading from Podanur to Coimbatore!

2294
02:23:36,791 --> 02:23:39,375
Target is the I&amp;B minister!
It'll explode on arrival!

2295
02:23:39,500 --> 02:23:42,250
Contact the station master now
and have him stop the train!

2296
02:23:42,375 --> 02:23:43,375
Roger that, sir!

2297
02:23:44,041 --> 02:23:45,166
Where are the students?

2298
02:23:46,250 --> 02:23:47,750
They just talk tough, ma'am.

2299
02:23:49,250 --> 02:23:51,875
Give them a mic,
and they'll ramble for hours!

2300
02:23:53,875 --> 02:23:56,291
You can get going.
Why needlessly waste your time?

2301
02:23:56,416 --> 02:23:58,875
Sir?
-Have an escort ready for Ma'am.

2302
02:23:59,000 --> 02:24:00,000
Chief...
-Yes, sir.

2303
02:24:02,875 --> 02:24:03,875
My resignation.

2304
02:24:05,750 --> 02:24:06,750
What the hell, man?

2305
02:24:06,875 --> 02:24:08,125
No sense of timing!

2306
02:24:09,125 --> 02:24:10,291
Not the time for all this!

2307
02:24:10,750 --> 02:24:12,000
What is the problem, Mr. Rao?

2308
02:24:12,500 --> 02:24:13,500
Ma'am...

2309
02:24:13,625 --> 02:24:15,041
There's still two hours left.

2310
02:24:15,625 --> 02:24:17,375
You've given your word.
Please uphold it.

2311
02:24:35,666 --> 02:24:36,750
Why didn't the train stop?

2312
02:24:37,250 --> 02:24:38,250
Come in, RTO!

2313
02:24:38,875 --> 02:24:39,875
What the hell!

2314
02:24:40,000 --> 02:24:41,000
Soldiers!

2315
02:24:44,291 --> 02:24:46,416
'Fire up your intellect
and make your foes tremble'

2316
02:24:46,541 --> 02:24:47,541
(Malayalam) Hurry!

2317
02:24:47,666 --> 02:24:50,125
'Sharpen your core
and erupt like a volcano'

2318
02:24:50,250 --> 02:24:52,125
'Ours is a great army'

2319
02:24:52,875 --> 02:24:55,000
'Bear witness, for ours is a great army'

2320
02:24:56,625 --> 02:24:57,875
You are late, Major!

2321
02:24:58,000 --> 02:25:00,000
(Malayalam) You told me to be late!

2322
02:25:00,125 --> 02:25:01,375
(Malayalam) Didn't I tell you?

2323
02:25:01,500 --> 02:25:03,875
That you'd salute me one day?

2324
02:25:04,000 --> 02:25:05,791
You'll salute this Major one day!

2325
02:25:07,125 --> 02:25:08,125
Go ahead!

2326
02:25:11,500 --> 02:25:12,500
Arms down!

2327
02:25:13,125 --> 02:25:14,125
Operation over!

2328
02:25:14,916 --> 02:25:17,791
From this moment,
we commence a rescue operation!

2329
02:25:17,916 --> 02:25:18,916
Dismissed!

2330
02:25:25,750 --> 02:25:27,125
Two hours are up, Mr. Rao.

2331
02:25:27,750 --> 02:25:28,750
I must leave.

2332
02:25:29,166 --> 02:25:30,500
Namaste.
-Namaste, ma'am.

2333
02:25:48,166 --> 02:25:51,916
Long Live Hindi!

2334
02:25:52,041 --> 02:25:54,625
Long Live Hindi!

2335
02:26:25,541 --> 02:26:27,125
I'll give the red signal.
Okay, sir.

2336
02:26:28,125 --> 02:26:32,000
No matter what, Ma'am does not leave
this station without hearing our voice.

2337
02:26:32,125 --> 02:26:33,250
Yes, Shariffa!

2338
02:26:33,375 --> 02:26:34,666
Take care, Brother Thambi.

2339
02:26:34,791 --> 02:26:36,125
I got this. Go on!

2340
02:26:51,666 --> 02:26:52,875
You can sit here, ma'am.

2341
02:26:57,250 --> 02:26:58,875
The train will be here soon, ma'am.

2342
02:27:17,375 --> 02:27:18,541
Why isn't the train here yet?

2343
02:27:19,500 --> 02:27:20,500
What is the problem?

2344
02:27:20,625 --> 02:27:21,875
It'll be here any moment.

2345
02:27:22,000 --> 02:27:23,000
What the hell, man?

2346
02:28:24,875 --> 02:28:28,125
Know what happens when you try
to restrain combustive material?

2347
02:28:29,916 --> 02:28:30,916
Blowback!

2348
02:28:33,375 --> 02:28:34,375
Very well.

2349
02:28:35,000 --> 02:28:36,000
Let's die together!

2350
02:28:37,125 --> 02:28:39,166
Let those signatures go up in smoke
with us!

2351
02:29:01,250 --> 02:29:03,791
No matter what you do
or however long you take...

2352
02:29:03,916 --> 02:29:05,375
...we'll just keep coming!

2353
02:29:05,791 --> 02:29:06,791
Bring it on!

2354
02:29:06,916 --> 02:29:08,875
Our grandchildren will be ready for you!

2355
02:30:16,666 --> 02:30:17,666
Charge!

2356
02:30:17,791 --> 02:30:19,125
Come on!

2357
02:30:19,250 --> 02:30:20,666
What are you doing?
Restrain them!

2358
02:30:20,791 --> 02:30:22,750
Restrain them!
-Come on!

2359
02:30:22,875 --> 02:30:24,375
Come on!
-Hurry!

2360
02:30:24,500 --> 02:30:26,791
Get it all out!
-Hurry!

2361
02:30:26,916 --> 02:30:28,875
This way!
-Ma'am!

2362
02:30:29,000 --> 02:30:30,250
Please, ma'am!

2363
02:30:30,375 --> 02:30:31,375
Ma'am!

2364
02:30:34,416 --> 02:30:36,625
(Kannada) Signatures from the land
of Basavanna!

2365
02:30:36,750 --> 02:30:38,416
Signatures from the land
of Basavanna!

2366
02:30:38,541 --> 02:30:39,875
The Father of Democracy!

2367
02:30:40,000 --> 02:30:43,666
Bangalore, Gulbarga, Hubli, Davangere,
Tumkur, Chikmanglur, Mangalore, Mysore!

2368
02:30:43,791 --> 02:30:46,500
(Karnataka) The entire Mysore State!
-The whole of Mysore!

2369
02:30:46,625 --> 02:30:48,125
Get it? All of Mysore, it seems!

2370
02:30:49,250 --> 02:30:50,250
Pull it up!

2371
02:30:51,250 --> 02:30:52,625
Does this script look the same?

2372
02:30:58,500 --> 02:30:59,500
Yes.

2373
02:31:00,791 --> 02:31:02,000
It looks all the same to me.

2374
02:31:02,125 --> 02:31:03,500
This is a very different language.

2375
02:31:03,625 --> 02:31:05,875
These are from my neighboring state.
Andhra Pradesh.

2376
02:31:06,000 --> 02:31:08,000
Telugu, ma'am! Telugu!
-Yes, ma'am!

2377
02:31:08,125 --> 02:31:10,750
Yes, ma'am. They look alike,
but they're different languages!

2378
02:31:13,250 --> 02:31:15,000
(Bengali) This is Bengali, ma'am!

2379
02:31:16,125 --> 02:31:20,916
(Bengali) 'Even if no one
rallies behind you, walk on alone'

2380
02:31:21,541 --> 02:31:25,000
(Bengali) 'Walk on alone'

2381
02:31:25,750 --> 02:31:27,500
But we are not alone here, ma'am!

2382
02:31:28,875 --> 02:31:30,291
All the languages are here!

2383
02:31:31,125 --> 02:31:33,875
All the languages!
All the languages!

2384
02:31:34,500 --> 02:31:36,250
(Malayalam) I'm Malayali, ma'am.

2385
02:31:36,375 --> 02:31:38,166
(Malayalam) These are from Kerala.

2386
02:31:38,291 --> 02:31:40,916
Malayalam! Malayalam! Malayalam!

2387
02:31:41,625 --> 02:31:43,875
This letter came from Madras,
ma'am.

2388
02:31:45,416 --> 02:31:46,666
First daughter's mark sheet.

2389
02:31:47,625 --> 02:31:49,125
Younger daughter's name?

2390
02:31:49,250 --> 02:31:50,250
Named after you!

2391
02:31:50,916 --> 02:31:51,916
Yes, ma'am.

2392
02:31:52,416 --> 02:31:54,375
Two daughters futures in your hands,
ma'am.

2393
02:32:03,666 --> 02:32:04,916
Sir!

2394
02:32:05,500 --> 02:32:06,750
Let's get you to the hospital!

2395
02:32:11,916 --> 02:32:13,000
Let's go to the hospital!

2396
02:32:13,125 --> 02:32:14,125
Why?

2397
02:32:15,250 --> 02:32:17,416
You expect to get
an award for Best Nurse?

2398
02:32:20,750 --> 02:32:24,166
No mongrel will dare question my loyalty.

2399
02:32:30,250 --> 02:32:32,500
Is this Hindi?
Can you please read and tell?

2400
02:32:33,875 --> 02:32:34,875
This is Marathi.

2401
02:32:35,000 --> 02:32:37,500
Marathi! Marathi! Marathi!

2402
02:32:41,000 --> 02:32:42,000
Tamil!

2403
02:32:43,750 --> 02:32:44,750
Chezhiya!

2404
02:32:46,750 --> 02:32:48,000
Tamil, ma'am...

2405
02:32:49,541 --> 02:32:51,000
Help him up!
-Chezhiya!

2406
02:32:51,125 --> 02:32:52,375
Get him up!

2407
02:32:52,500 --> 02:32:53,666
Ma'am!

2408
02:32:53,791 --> 02:32:55,875
It was wrong of us to even ask them
for signatures!

2409
02:32:58,500 --> 02:33:00,000
What can illiterate citizens do?

2410
02:33:01,250 --> 02:33:02,291
To show their support...

2411
02:33:03,291 --> 02:33:04,750
...they sent their ration cards.

2412
02:33:09,375 --> 02:33:10,875
(Hindi) Their means of sustenance.

2413
02:33:11,375 --> 02:33:12,541
That's what they sent over.

2414
02:33:15,791 --> 02:33:18,250
What more evidence do you need
for public support?

2415
02:33:20,750 --> 02:33:22,666
Do we have to bring over the people
who sent these?

2416
02:33:25,500 --> 02:33:27,875
Your people blocked every path
on their journey.

2417
02:33:29,375 --> 02:33:30,666
The ones who surpassed it?

2418
02:33:31,875 --> 02:33:33,000
They were shot to death.

2419
02:33:34,500 --> 02:33:39,000
"As hard as it'd be for North Indians,
if Tamil is legally forced on them..."

2420
02:33:39,125 --> 02:33:41,125
"...that's how it's like
for us to learn Hindi."

2421
02:33:42,000 --> 02:33:44,875
Lullabies of our mothers,
stories of our grandmothers...

2422
02:33:45,000 --> 02:33:46,625
'Wisdom of our grandfathers..."

2423
02:33:46,750 --> 02:33:48,875
"Our education, literature, music..."

2424
02:33:49,000 --> 02:33:51,125
"All of it is etched in our blood!"

2425
02:33:51,875 --> 02:33:55,625
As you can't take the language out
of our blood, you intend to make us bleed?

2426
02:33:57,750 --> 02:34:01,875
"To show your support for Tamil,
assemble at the Coimbatore Junction!"

2427
02:34:02,000 --> 02:34:04,500
"The futures of the students
are in your hands!"

2428
02:34:04,625 --> 02:34:06,375
"Your future is in your hands!"

2429
02:34:08,250 --> 02:34:10,041
As of now,
we'll stop this protest.

2430
02:34:13,000 --> 02:34:15,000
We've done everything we could.

2431
02:34:18,166 --> 02:34:20,000
What do you intend to do, ma'am?

2432
02:34:22,375 --> 02:34:24,750
He says he's done what he could do.
It's up to you now.

2433
02:34:32,166 --> 02:34:33,666
"Our bodies may fall."

2434
02:34:34,166 --> 02:34:35,791
"But our linguistic pride never will!"

2435
02:34:35,916 --> 02:34:37,375
"Our voices will not abate!"

2436
02:34:37,791 --> 02:34:40,166
Until the last Tamilian is left,
it will echo far and wide!

2437
02:34:40,625 --> 02:34:43,375
"Our bodies, for this soil.
Our lives, for Tamil!"

2438
02:34:43,500 --> 02:34:44,541
Long Live Tamil!

2439
02:34:45,791 --> 02:34:46,791
Victory to Tamilians!

2440
02:34:46,916 --> 02:34:48,291
"Victory to Tamilians!"

2441
02:34:56,125 --> 02:34:59,041
"I give my word to the students
of this nation!"

2442
02:34:59,500 --> 02:35:02,250
The promises of our late great
Prime Minister...

2443
02:35:03,250 --> 02:35:07,000
...will continue to be upheld
wholeheartedly!

2444
02:35:07,125 --> 02:35:10,541
"Every state is free to choose
their own official language."

2445
02:35:10,666 --> 02:35:15,375
"Be it through their regional language
or English..."

2446
02:35:16,291 --> 02:35:19,916
"...they have complete freedom
to conduct their official business!"

2447
02:35:20,750 --> 02:35:23,750
"If even one non-Hindi speaking
state..."

2448
02:35:23,875 --> 02:35:28,666
"...voices its displeasure against
making Hindi the sole official language..."

2449
02:35:29,375 --> 02:35:31,250
"...the bill will not be passed."

2450
02:35:31,916 --> 02:35:38,041
"I firmly state that English will continue
to be recognized as an official language!"

2451
02:35:41,291 --> 02:35:45,375
Should the legislative assembly be convened
hastily because the students ask so?

2452
02:35:45,500 --> 02:35:46,625
Who are students?

2453
02:35:47,000 --> 02:35:48,250
The blood of our blood.

2454
02:35:48,375 --> 02:35:49,750
The flesh of our flesh.

2455
02:35:49,875 --> 02:35:51,125
The soul of our future!

2456
02:35:53,625 --> 02:35:55,166
What about the train they burned down?

2457
02:35:56,166 --> 02:35:58,875
A few burnt train coaches
can be rebuilt.

2458
02:35:59,791 --> 02:36:02,625
But if the lives of students
are destroyed...

2459
02:36:02,750 --> 02:36:04,125
...can it be reclaimed?

2460
02:36:07,750 --> 02:36:11,750
"We disregard the Official Languages Act
in all schools of Tamil Nadu."

2461
02:36:12,291 --> 02:36:17,791
"This assembly decrees Tamil and English
to be the official mediums of instruction."

2462
02:36:24,041 --> 02:36:25,375
Long Live Tamil!

2463
02:36:26,750 --> 02:36:27,750
Long Live Tamil!

2464
02:36:31,625 --> 02:36:33,125
Long Live Tamil!

2465
02:36:52,375 --> 02:36:55,875
"A statue immortalizing comrade Rajendran,
who succumbed to police gunfire..."

2466
02:36:56,000 --> 02:36:59,125
"...has been erected at the entrance
of his alma mater."

2467
02:37:48,916 --> 02:37:51,375
'O army of comrades'

2468
02:37:51,500 --> 02:37:53,750
'Let's go to war'

2469
02:37:53,875 --> 02:37:56,166
'Be it life or death...'

2470
02:37:56,291 --> 02:37:58,500
'...we shall face it together'

2471
02:37:58,625 --> 02:38:03,375
'With courage,
we will seek answers'

2472
02:38:03,500 --> 02:38:07,500
'As a roaring wildfire,
we will reclaim justice'

2473
02:38:08,291 --> 02:38:12,916
'Without seeing the light of change,
these eyes shall sleep not'

2474
02:38:13,041 --> 02:38:17,625
'Even if bullets pierce our chests,
our quest for truth will cease not'

2475
02:38:17,750 --> 02:38:20,250
'No change comes about on its own'

2476
02:38:20,375 --> 02:38:22,625
'We will guard our motherland
now and forever'

2477
02:38:22,750 --> 02:38:24,916
'We took to arms that day'

2478
02:38:25,041 --> 02:38:27,375
'Even a calf will pounce in an attack'

2479
02:38:27,500 --> 02:38:29,875
'A needless, needless law...'

2480
02:38:30,000 --> 02:38:32,166
'Won't the arrogance
of those in power fall?'

2481
02:38:32,291 --> 02:38:34,375
'Our blood boils to stir us on'

2482
02:38:34,500 --> 02:38:36,625
'A war of blazing passion'

2483
02:38:39,166 --> 02:38:41,416
'How is it right to relinquish
what belongs to us?'

2484
02:38:41,541 --> 02:38:43,875
'Vanquishing oppressors
